title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Form into balls. Refrigerate these balls until firm.
Melt together in double boiler the last 3 ingredients.
Remove balls from refrigerator and dip balls in chocolate mixture by holding them with toothpicks. Place on waxed paper and freeze until chocolate is hard.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: date pudding
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; then beat in eggs.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Pour in a greased and floured small square Pyrex pan.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruits and slice cherries in half.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve in your most beautiful cut glass bowl.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients, adding pineapple last.
Put in unbaked pie crust. Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
These pies freeze well.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cut butter into flour; stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine cheese and sugar and fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust and chill.
Combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: green beans with sour cream sauce
directions: Preparation: Wash, trim and French-cut diagonally cut whole beans into inch lengths.
Cook in boiling saltwater for 5 to 7 minutes for French or 10 to 15 minutes for 2-inch pieces until tender-crisp.
Drain well.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, syrup and softened butter in blender. Mix well. Remove from blender and stir in nuts with a spoon. Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Can be frozen.

title: zesty tomato cups
directions: Combine eggs, crumbs, cheese, garlic, thyme, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add spinach, celery and onions.
Mix well. Cut tomatoes crosswise. Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Using a sharp knife, make a sawtooth cut around the edges of the shells.
Spoon mixture into the shells.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a pan mix soup, nutmeg and water.
Add raw rice to soup mixture and stir.
Lay chicken on top; skin side up.
Dribble butter across top.
Sprinkle each part of chicken with salt and paprika.
Cover with foil and put in 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours. Remove foil and turn to 350° and let cook about 1/2 hour more. Let sit about 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: panamanian chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (except tomato paste and browning sauce) and marinate overnight.
Fry chicken pieces; drain oil.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken plus 3 to 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil, then let simmer until enough water is left to make a gravy. At this time, add the tomato paste and browning sauce.
Simmer until gravy thickens.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled (uncut) potatoes in salted water until tender. Drain. Add butter, sour cream and cream cheese and mash until smooth. Beat in remaining ingredients. Place in refrigerator and use within two weeks. Makes 12 servings.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until blended.
Sprinkle chili powder over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Serve with crackers, Waverly or Town House.

title: champagne apricot
directions: If you want to get a party started and you want a surprise, make this Champagne Apricot.
"This is really bordering on a love potion," so says Trader Vic.

title: jeweled pineapple dessert
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to make 2 cups. Heat; dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add lemon juice; cool until syrupy. Mix apples, pineapple, oranges and nuts together; add to gelatin. Chill until firm. Serve with Fluffy Orange Dressing.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch pan (or glass bowl).
Add the celery, green pepper, red onion and peas in layers.
Cover with mayonnaise, sealing edges.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Then add shredded cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes, onions and peppers into small thin rings.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, salt, pepper, carrot, sour cream and soup.
Melt butter in pan and mix in stuffing.
Take 1/2 of stuffing out of pan.
Pour in squash and top with other 1/2 of stuffing.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Make in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each in cinnamon and white sugar.
Put in greased tube pan.
Melt the margarine, brown sugar and nuts together; pour over biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In deep bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour into dry ingredients. Stir with a whisk until batter is smooth.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large pot, boil chicken breasts; season to taste.
Cook until done.
Remove chicken from pot, debone and shred.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter or margarine.
Add to cooked spaghetti, sauteed onion and bell pepper, Velveeta, Ro-Tel and shredded chicken.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted and sauce is thick.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburg pops
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.

Divide into 8 portions and shape each portion around a skewer, having it look more or less like a drumstick with a third of the skewer sticking out like a bone. Spread the meat with the mustard, your fingers are the best tool for this.
Now roll each portion in the crumbs, pressing it all around.
Sprinkle with the shortening and bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes or until brown or fry on all sides in a skillet, using a little more shortening.

title: creamy coconut
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add oleo, flour, milk, vanilla and almond extract; mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups of coconut and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup coconut. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel frosting(50 years old)
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well with hand. (Now mixer.)
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add cream mixture; beat well.
Cook in heavy, large saucepan, stirring constantly, until it reaches a soft ball stage or 234°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cook 10 minutes.
Mix until thick enough to spread, approximately 10 minutes.
Spread on cooled cake.
(Can use mixer on medium speed now, if you like.)

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Add to onions, celery and water in a heavy kettle. Heat to boiling, cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring to a boil the syrup and brown sugar.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press this in a pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips and spread onto other mixture. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: em's chocolate cake
directions: Cook the 1/2 cup cocoa and hot water until thick and cool. Sift the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda together into a large mixing bowl.
Mix the buttermilk, oil and eggs in a small bowl, then pour into dry ingredients. Add the vanilla and cocoa mixture. Stir with a large whisk.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Freezes well.

title: upside-down peach cake
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick of butter.
Melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of cake pan (9-inches round by 3-inches deep).
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentric circles.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
In large bowl, beat remaining 1 1/2 sticks of butter with sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg yolks. Alternately beat in flour mixture with milk and vanilla until well blended.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil in a large mixing bowl and beat well.
Gradually beat in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots, nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: macaroni dessert
directions: Combine the first four ingredients with the reserved juices from the pineapple and oranges.
Cook the ingredients and cool. Cook macaroni and cool.
Combine cooled macaroni with sauce and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Add drained fruit and mix thoroughly, then add Cool Whip.
Top with drained cherries and keep refrigerated.
Makes a large bowl.

title: rosettes
directions: Stir and mix until sooth.
Heat rosette iron in deep fat at 375°.
Dip iron into batter and then into hot fat for 1 minute or until rosette is golden brown.
Lift out.
Tip to drain on absorbent paper.
May be dipped into powdered or granulated sugar.

title: knock your socks off rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line a large pie dish with bottom crust.
Brush with egg white.
Prick well with a fork.
In a large bowl, mix together eggs, sugar, flour, cooking oil, vanilla and chopped rhubarb. Pour in the filling and cover it with top crust.
Cut steam vents. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for an additional 40 minutes or until the pie is done.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Put remainder of ingredients in medium bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: zesty chicken-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Stir together macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites, oil, milk and 1 can of coconut. Bake in greased sheet pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Make holes in warm cake with fork; pour cream of coconut over cake.
When cool, combine second can of coconut with whipped topping and frost cake still in pan.
Chill several hours and serve.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add crumbs and mix.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Add coconut and nuts and blend together. Grease and flour a tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding and 1/2 cup milk together, then add the rest of milk and beat with mixer for 5 minutes.
Spread over cake.
Drain 2 small cans crushed pineapple and spread over that.
Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: nana's easy apple cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Measure and sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Prepare apples.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add vanilla and apples. Place all in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. After cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: pecan pull apart
directions: Melt butter, let stand.
Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and put 1/3 of dry ingredients in bottom of pan.
Put 12 rolls on dry ingredients.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Pour 1/3 melted butter over rolls and 1/3 of dry mixtures.
Put 12 more rolls; sprinkle cinnamon.
Put rest of dry mixture.
Put rest of butter.
Cover with wet paper towel.
Let rise overnight at room temperature. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: italian roast chicken and potatoes
directions: You determine the quantities according to your needs.

title: tuna fish sauce
directions: Mix and cook everything except tuna fish.
Add tuna fish last hour.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry ring salad
directions: Wash cranberries.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Cook until tender. Add sugar and cook for 5 minutes.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Dissolve in hot cranberries and add salt.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add nuts and celery.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into oiled ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and place on large salad plate.
Place light lettuce around salad or pour into a square Pyrex pan or a bowl and serve.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and chill thoroughly.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Thaw and thoroughly drain broccoli and peas.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream or onion dip.
Stir into vegetables until moistened.
Add chopped eggs and mix lightly.
Serves 6-8.

title: italian noodle soup
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic slowly in oil.
Add water and tomato paste; simmer until meat is tender (about 2 hours).
Add noodles and stir gently.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jam cookie
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugar, salt, vanilla and egg; beat until creamy.
Stir in sifted flour.
Drop by teaspoon and make a small dent and fill with jam.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until well blended.
Add onions, beef, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Mix well.
Make into a ball.
Sprinkle chili powder on wax paper. Roll cheese ball into it until the whole ball is covered.
Cover bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.
(Serve with crackers.)

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use large (oblong) casserole dish.
Put a thin layer each of lettuce, green onions and bell pepper.
Cover with English peas and salad dressing.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with bacon bits.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill.

title: bacon cheddar potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small chunks or strips. Boil until slightly tender. Do not overcook. Drain some of the water, leaving about 1/2 to 1-inch of water from the cooked potatoes. Add jar of Ragu sauce, salt and pepper to taste and onion salt. Let simmer for about 10 minutes in crock-pot or on stove top. Top with bacon bits and shredded cheese when ready to serve.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: *Eggs and shortening must be at room temperature.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soup, water and rice together; pour over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Bring tomato soup to a boil in a saucepan.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water in a bowl.
In a another bowl combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add gelatine mixture to tomato soup, then add cream cheese mixture.
Mix well and then add celery, onions and shrimp.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef roast or grill
directions: Place meat in shallow glass container.
Saute garlic in oil; blend in next 4 ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Add Worcestershire sauce and catsup to marinade.
Cover and place in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Cook on grill, turning frequently and baste with marinade 35 to 40 minutes, depending on doneness desired.

title: lamb patties
directions: Combine lamb, onion, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Shape into 4 thin patties.
Place 1 tablespoon Bleu cheese on each of 2 patties.
Cover with remaining patties.
Seal edges.
Place on broiler rack 3 to 4-inches from heat.
Broil 6 minutes or until browned on 1 side.
Turn once and broil 3 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: jigglers gelatin snacks(recipe from jell-o)
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill at least 3 hours. Jigglers will be firm after 1 hour, but may be difficult to remove from pan.
To cut Jigglers, dip bottom of pan in warm water for 15 seconds to loosen gelatin.
Cut shapes with cookie cutters all the way through the gelatin.
Lift from the pan with index finger or metal spatula.

title: fresh peach daiquiri
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender with 2 to 3 ice cubes.
Blend 30 seconds or until smooth.

title: chunky fruit mix
directions: Drain fruit, but save pineapple juice and thicken with vanilla pudding and Tang. Mix fruit and juice mixture together. Chill.

title: cream-style lima beans with mushrooms
directions: Combine liquid from mushrooms, plus enough water to cook lima beans.
Add beans, onion, sugar and salt.
Cook until beans are tender.
Stir in mushrooms and cream; heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs, zucchini and extract.
Add dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Place in 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 12-inch casserole.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: taco turkey rice
directions: Cook turkey until lightly browned; drain.
Add tomatoes and seasoning mix.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn and peppers.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with cheese, tortilla chips and sour cream if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bigos-polish festival favorite
directions: Boil meat to make enough broth to cover about 1 inch of a large pot.
Layer cabbage, then onions, then apples and dot each layer with butter or margarine.
Cut up meat and lay on top.
Continue layers until the meat and vegetables are used.
Cook on stove on medium heat until cabbage and onions are tender.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, sour cream, 1/2 of cheese and 1 cup of onions.
Pour in dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: blueberry grape salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and add remaining ingredients.
Let jell.

title: thick white gravy
directions: In a pot, combine butter with flour, thoroughly.
Add milk gradually, stirring vigorously.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Add salt.
Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Yields approximately 1 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix until well blended; add remaining ingredients.
Chill, then roll in chopped walnuts.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil, dill weed and Ranch dressing well.
Cover crackers and spread on cookie sheet.
Let dry 1/2 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then drain.
Shake up sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Pour over all vegetables and macaroni; marinate overnight.
Delicious!

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Combine bread stuffing with mushrooms and juice, butter and cheese.
Spread over flank steak.
Roll up like jelly roll. Fasten with skewers or string.
Pour oil in slow cooking crock-pot.
Roll steak in oil, coating all sides.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 50 minutes at 350° in a preheated oven.

title: mexican stew
directions: Cook the suet in a kettle over medium heat until fat is rendered.
Roll the beef in flour and add to suet.
Cook, stirring, until brown.
Add the water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the beef is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until the vegetables are tender.

title: fruit balls
directions: Melt butter.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add dates; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cook; add nuts, cherries, Krispies and flavoring.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar and shortening. Add eggs, sorghum or honey and buttermilk. Sift together remaining ingredients; add to sugar, shortening and egg mixture and blend well. Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, greased and lightly floured, 30 to 40 minutes. Test for doneness; insert a wooden pick in center.
It should remove cleanly.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together the first six ingredients.
Sieve together flour, soda and salt.
Add to dry ingredients, the cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add nuts and raisins.
Fold in vanilla.
Pour into a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Makes 16 servings.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix everything together except the noodles and cheese.
In a baking pan, lay 1 layer of noodles and add some of the turkey mixture.
Then add cheese on top.
Repeat these steps until all gone.
End with cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add strawberries and pineapple; cool until like honey.
Mash bananas. Add to above.
Pour 1/2 in bowl and add sour cream and remainder of jello.

title: grace smith's dip
directions: Mix first two ingredients (defrost guacamole dip and soften cream cheese).
Spread on tray.
Layer on top the chopped vegetables.
Top with taco sauce.
Serve with Ritz crackers and corn chips.

title: creamy hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container. Use 1/3 cup of the mixture in a cup and finish filling with boiling water.

title: old fashioned banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in mixer or by hand, but mix well. Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until it tests done with a toothpick.
Ice with "Philly" cream cheese icing.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 8 or 7 x 11 baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour into baking dish. Bake approx. 45 minutes at 350°. Don't overcook.

title: chicken liver paste
directions: *One egg to carton of livers.

title: lynda's frittata(low-fat)
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch microwave dish, saute the onion, pepper and potatoes in olive oil for 3 minutes. Fold in whipped egg whites. Fold in egg yolks.
Add to other ingredients in dish.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.

title: maggie's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour, sifted with cream of tartar and soda.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll very thin and bake at 375° until very lightly browned.
(Dough can be re-rolled.)
Trim with outlines of confectioners sugar icing and trim with sugar and non-pareils.

title: scalloped onions, leeks and shallots
directions: In a heavy kettle, cook the onions, leeks and shallots in the butter with salt and pepper to taste, covered, over moderate heat, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderately low and cook vegetables, stirring occasionally for 10 to 20 minutes more or until soft.
Remove lid and cook mixture over moderate heat, stirring for 3 to 5 minutes more or until excess liquid is evaporated.
Onion mixture may be made 2 days in advance and kept covered and chilled.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Combine flour, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese and coat chicken breasts in that mixture.
Brown coated chicken with 1/2 stick of butter.
After first turn add salt and pepper.
After chicken is browned, remove to rimmed baking dish.
Now put 1/3 stick of butter in frypan and using spatula scrape bottom of pan. Put in mushrooms and stir until they're coated and shrink a little.
Add 16 ounce bottle of Marsala cooking wine and turn heat to medium-high.
When liquid starts to bubble, add 1 1/2 tablespoons of flour mixture and 1/4 cup milk.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes, then add to baking dish and warm in oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, mix chicken broth, onion, basil, oregano, bay leaf and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in vegetables.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp.
Throw away bay leaf.
Stir in chicken and undrained tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 main dish servings.

title: zucchini beef bake
directions: Wash and cut off ends of squash. Cut in 1/4-inch slices. Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes or until tender and drain. In skillet, cook meat with onion until brown; drain fat. Stir in 1/2 cup bread crumbs, salt, thyme, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and garlic powder to taste, if desired. Remove from heat. In saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter; blend in flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Add milk all at once. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add cheese; stir until melted. Add meat mixture. Place half of squash in 2-quart baking dish. Pour half the cheese mixture. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt shortening in warm buttermilk.
Add sugar, salt and soda to warm buttermilk mixture. It will foam up.
Add this to yeast, then add flour.
Add more flour if needed.
Knead dough and then cover with bowl.
Wait 15 minutes.
Make rolls or loaves and let rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
If in loaves, bake until when patted sounds hollow.

title: thymed tuna-bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, oil, thyme, sugar and black pepper.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Whisk dressing. Toss in beans, celery, carrots, onion and celery leaves.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt butter; brown onion.
Melt cheese.
Add mushrooms, soup, garlic and drained broccoli; mix well.
Cover with almonds.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash in salted water until tender.
Mash. Add soup, cornbread, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix and put in casserole.
Bake until brown at 375°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake according to directions, except use juice for the water.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.
Top with the crushed pineapple evenly over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top when partly cool with powdered sugar.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken with a bay leaf, stock of celery with leaves, onion, peppercorns and parsley until tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from broth; remove skin, bones and fat.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Remove from broth and add the rest of ingredients. Cook and simmer 30 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Bring soaked peas to a boil, adding water if necessary. Reduce heat, add ham bone and pepper.
Cover and simmer one hour. Add celery, carrot and onion.
Simmer one hour longer.
Remove ham bone.
Pull off meat and shred it finely.
Return meat shreds to soup and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Mix together the garden peas, water chestnuts, onion and cream of mushroom soup. Put in buttered 8-inch baking dish.
Spread grated cheese on top of mixture.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Bake 45 minutes at 400° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sugar-free coney sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in large skillet until thoroughly browned. Drain. Add tomato puree and stir thoroughly.
Stir in Diet Coke, cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Then remove cover and cook to desired consistency.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Cook on simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: trail pockets
directions: Lightly brown
ground
beef.
Add
green onion and bell pepper; saute
until
onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except the 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Simmer about 10 minutes until
it
thickens.
Remove from heat and let cool 10 minutes. Stir
in cheese and set aside.
Do not overcook this mixture.

title: peanut butter-n-jelly(kids recipe #5))
directions: Put peanut butter and jelly on bread with the knife
Smash the 2 pieces of bread together.

title: barbecued leg of lamb
directions: Mix everything together, except lamb.
Spread on the lamb. Marinate for 4 to 5 hours.
Grill over hot coals about 1/2 hour on each side.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Prepare one recipe of rice.
While rice is cooking, pound chicken breast out flat.
Salt, pepper, sage and flour one side. Add one teaspoon cooked rice to unfloured side and roll up.
Brown in a little oil.
Take chicken out of skillet.
Make tomato gravy with drippings and tomato sauce.
Add chicken to gravy and cover. Let steam a few minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hershey's black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (or until cake tester comes out clean).
Cool completely; frost.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Add onions, celery and bell pepper to 2 sticks margarine. Saute until cooked.
Add flour and cook with cover on low for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add parsley and crawfish and cook 15 minutes.
Stir.
Add half and half, half of Velveeta, jalapeno relish, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken marco polo casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with chicken breasts.
Mix remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.

title: marinated grilled flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients in the pan in which the meat is to be marinated.
Marinate steak, turning occasionally, for 2 to 12 hours in the refrigerator.
Broil meat over hot coals for 5 minutes per side for rare meat or cook until desired doneness. Slice meat on a diagonal across the grain and serve.
Great for summer on the grill.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: avocado salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients except avocados.
Dice avocados and gently toss in vinegar and spice mix.
Serve with tortilla chips, chicken or seafood.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, chopped boiled eggs and vegetables.
Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and add to mixture.
Mix all ingredients and add salt to taste.

title: zucchini milk bread pudding
directions: Bring zucchini milk to a boil.
Pour over bread crumbs; add oleo.
Combine honey, salt and egg; add to bread mixture.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Place in 1-quart greased bowl, set in shallow pan with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Put favorite pieces of chicken in baking dish. Drizzle good with tomato catsup, brown sugar and soup mix. Add orange juice and orange peel, then soy sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and cook approximately another 50 minutes. Ovens vary, so cook until browned and tender.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce leaves.
Chop tomatoes, cucumber, green onions and radishes.
Layer in a salad bowl beginning with lettuce in order listed.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar.
Let this sit in refrigerator for 1 hour; pour over salad.
Top with cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: mayo-parmesan bread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Stir in snipped chives or parsley, if desired.
Set aside.

title: party strawberries
directions: Combine condensed milk, dry unflavored gelatin, dry strawberry gelatin and food coloring in bowl; mix well.
Stir in coconut and chopped walnuts.
Form into shape of strawberries; dip tops into green sugar.
Roll in red sugar.
Chill until serving time. Yield:
24 servings.

title: raspberry wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of dish, spread broccoli over rice. Melt cheese, margarine and milk in microwave. Mix well and pour on top of broccoli and rice. Top with toasted bread crumbs (optional).

title: baked cabbage
directions: Quarter cabbage and remove the heart.

Butter each quarter with butter or margarine until all nooks and crannies are filled. Put quarters back in original places; wrap with aluminum foil. Place in a pan or ovenproof bowl and bake at 400° for 1 1/4 hours or until done to your taste.
Umm, umm good!!!!

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.

Stir in spaghetti sauce, oregano and garlic powder.	Meanwhile, combine Ricotta or cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg, salt, pepper and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Spoon 1/2 of sauce into 2-quart oblong glass baking dish.
Top with 4 noodles and cheese mixture.	Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.

title: peach jam
directions: Cook peaches and apples with water until tender.
Add orange juice and rind.
Add 1 cup sugar for each cup of pulp.
Cook for 30 minutes and pour into sterilized glasses.

title: maude's date pudding
directions: Mix ingredients until moist. Press in bowl. Sprinkle top with some graham cracker crumbs. Cover with Cool Whip and chill for 1 hour.

title: chitterlings(chit'lins)
directions: Wash chitterlings thoroughly and cover with boiling, salted water.
Add whole cloves and red pepper, cut into pieces.
Cook until tender and drain.
Cut in pieces about the size of an oyster.
Dip each piece in beaten egg and then in cracker crumbs. Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil fryer; save broth. Cook spaghetti in broth.

When spaghetti gets soft, drain broth and set aside. Saute onions, celery and peppers in butter until soft. Add mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and stewed tomatoes, then add cut chicken and spaghetti. Sprinkle grated cheese over top of dish. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber-cheese vegetable dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and whipping cream.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with assorted vegetables. Makes about 1 1/3 cups dip.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken for 30 minutes or until tender.
Cool and remove from bones.
Place chicken in a lightly buttered casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Toss crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in two 8-inch round or square dishes the refried beans. Pour taco sauce over beans.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream. Blend with chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Spread over taco sauce.
Chop the tomato and blot onto a paper towel to remove excess liquid.
Layer tomatoes over the sour cream.
Top with chopped green olives and shredded cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cranberry marble mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and stir in pineapple.
Chill until thick. Fold in cranberry sauce and sour cream over top and stir through to marble.

title: date bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, butter (softened), brown sugar and baking soda.
Press half into deep cookie sheet.
Boil water, sugar and dates for 5 minutes.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Add remainder of dry ingredients, press gently.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; knead in butter to form big ball.
This should give 24 biscuits.
Make mixture into smaller balls; place on greased baking sheet.
Flatten balls with either biscuit stamp or fork in shape of cross.
Bake in moderate oven for 20 minutes, until they start to brown.
Do not allow mixture to become too wet.

title: sharon's oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat oil and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by rounded cookie scoop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes before removing cookies from sheet to cooling rack.
Store in tightly closed container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen depending on cookie size.

title: wine burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand for at least 1/2 hour before charcoaling or broiling.
Should make 8 burgers, 1/4 pound each.

title: chicken bog for 100
directions: Boil chickens and chopped onions. Remove bones and skin. Measure broth so that you have twice as much broth as rice. Season broth.
Bring broth to a boil and add rice.
When it comes back to a boil, reduce heat and cook 30 minutes.

title: sausage filled wontons
directions: Heat 4-inches of oil at 350° in a saucepan. Crumble sausage into large skillet; add onion. Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; drain drippings. Stir in next 4 ingredients. Mix until cheeses melt. Lightly dampen 1 wrapper by dipping your finger in water and wiping all the edges, making 1/4-inch border around the square. Keep wonton wrappers from drying; cover remaining with a damp towel. Place rounded teaspoonful of sausage mixture in the middle of the wrapper. Fold wrapper over filling to form a triangle, sealing edges and removing air bubbles. Repeat with remaining wrappers and filling. Heat 4-inches of oil in a deep-fryer to 350°. Fry wontons a few at a time until golden, about 1 minute. Serve hot. Makes 30.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak navy beans overnight in water to cover.
Drain, then add fresh water to 1-inch above the top of the beans and cook until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 3 to 4 hours.
Uncover during the last hour.

title: cheese boats
directions: Brown hamburger.
Grate cheese and chop olives, onion and chilies.
Combine all ingredients.
Scoop out French rolls.
Fill each scooped out roll and wrap each in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger pie with french fries
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add meat. Brown lightly.
Add soup, catsup and seasonings.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange potatoes over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wayne's chili
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in small amount of margarine until tender.
Drain.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain. Mix Chili-O mix into ground beef thoroughly with a fork.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put raisins in bottom of a greased 1-quart casserole.
Dip bread slices in melted margarine and place on top of raisins.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla extract and milk and beat well.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Place casserole in pan of hot water and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream shortening, butter, vanilla and butter flavoring. Alternately add confectioners sugar and milk.
Beat on high for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the cherry pie filling in bottom of pan and sprinkle cake mix all over it.
Pour melted butter on top.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°. Delicious with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: tater tot casserole #2
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and put in bottom of dish along with chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Pour soup on top of ground beef.
Layer cheese on top, then place Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together. In separate bowl, combine egg, orange juice, rind, water and shortening. Mix into dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened. Add cranberries and nuts. Pour into greased 9X5X3 inch loaf pan.

title: turkey cabbage casserole
directions: Mix onion, sauces, tomato juice and spices.
Add to meat.
Top half of cabbage with meat mixture.
Repeat once more.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Preheat oven.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix well and put into greased small muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Heat in double boiler or heavy pan.
Boil 5 minutes. Excellent on ice cream or as fruit dip, especially apples.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, oleo and sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Mix strawberry jello and boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to gel.
Cream together cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust. Add strawberry mixture on top.
Chill and serve.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover.
Wash and drain beans.
To the two quarts of water, add beans and ham hocks. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add potato, onion and celery. Simmer an hour longer. Remove ham hocks.
Cut up meat and return meat to soup.
Remove 1 cup of beans with liquid.
Puree then return to soup.

title: vegetable supreme
directions: Chop vegetables (whatever kind you want) into bite sized pieces.
Place in pot with a small amount of water in bottom. Cover with tight fitting lid and steam until tender crisp stage.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut the squash lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Cut up onion and pepper and mix with the sausage.
Stuff in the hollow squash.
Pour tomato sauce over the tops.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce in bottom of dish.
I use my lasagna pan works great for a dish.
For second layer, chop desired amount of celery, chopped onion and green pepper.
Next add peas; then spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise, then Cheddar cheese and crumbled bacon.
This can be prepared ahead.

title: fish batter
directions: Beat eggs and spices together; add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Add 7-Up until dough is thin. Dip fish in flour and then in batter and fry.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve with your favorite salad dressing.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Boil and cool.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze.
To Serve:
Mix with pop.

title: chicken breast delicious
directions: Dip chicken in milk, then drag through crackers.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with soup and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick steam
directions: Using a large skillet, combine the ingredients together and cover for 10 minutes; stir frequently.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil. Cook rapidly for 12 to 15 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: best deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with mayonnaise.
Add relish, mustard, salt and pepper. Stir well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix butter, cheese, flour, red pepper and salt.
Shape into little balls and press pecan half on top.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: dorothy brown's raw apple cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except flour, together.
Add the flour; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 1-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes (until done when tested) in a 325° oven.
Frost when cool, but slightly warm.

title: baked corn
directions: Add all ingredients together in baking dish. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Stir once when you see it starting to thicken around edges.

title: crumbly apple pie
directions: Mix white sugar, cinnamon, salt and apple slices in large bowl.
Arrange in pie shell.
Mix brown sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
You can cut thin slices of pie crust and weave in and out on top of pie.
Press ends together.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until apple juice bubbles.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over the melted butter.
Arrange the peaches on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, cream cheese, pimento cheese and Cheddar cheese in bowl; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans, coating well. Chill wrapped in plastic wrap until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and carrots and mix with electric mixer.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart covered microwavable casserole.
Cook, covered, for 9 to 10 minutes at power level 6, or until heated through.
Stir once halfway through cooking.
Stir well.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crisp raw vegetables.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Put milk, banana (in half), vanilla, ice cubes and sugar, if desired, into blender and blend for about 20 to 30 seconds.
Pour into glass and serve.

title: chicken tarragon delight
directions: If you can, select boned chicken thighs.
Dip in batter of egg and milk; roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place thighs in buttered baking dish or casserole so they are not too crowded.
Cover with the sweet cream and wine.
Sprinkle the fresh or dried tarragon generously over chicken, then the Parmesan, salt and pepper, parsley and a few dashes of paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Check occasionally to see that cream is not cooking down too rapidly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Place in 2 1/2 qt. greased casserole dish.
Toss topping of corn flakes or potato chips with 1/4 cup butter.
Pat on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are done. Based on 10 servings.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add oatmeal-water mixture.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 55 minutes in greased pan.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Stir in honey and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well. Stir in nuts and fruit.
Chill several hours.

title: dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add Ro-Tel and cream of chicken soup. Stir and mix in Velveeta.
Add "hot" to taste.

title: barbecue sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, egg, bread crumbs and sage.
Form into balls. Brown and remove drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Add meat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Time:
50 minutes. Makes approximately 30 balls.

title: cranberry salad(serves 8)
directions: Chop cranberries and add sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to prepare salad, add rest of ingredients.
You may omit the nondairy whip topping if you like and it still is really good.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add milk, margarine and eggs. Cook until thick.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti until desired texture.
As spaghetti boils, prepare other ingredients.
Cut cucumber, onion and olives. Remove seeds from the cucumber.
Place them in a bowl.
Pour 1/4 Zesty Italian over them; let sit.
When spaghetti is done, rinse and place in bowl with other ingredients.
Pour the remaining Zesty Italian over it.
Stir up; chill.
Before serving, add cherry tomatoes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread cubes in buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar and oil; mix until light yellow.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture.
This will be very stiff.
Add vanilla, stirring until well mixed.
Add apples and walnuts; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: linguine with shrimp
directions: Cook linguine.
Set aside.
Heat dressing.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Cook and stir for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add linguine. Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: peppermint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and flavorings.
Mix flour and candy.
Roll into small balls and dip each into egg white.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Put a chocolate chip in center of each.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: enchiladas
directions: In a skillet, heat oil until warm.
Place a tortilla in oil until soft (do not fry them until they are crispy).
Shake off excess oil.
Lay tortillas flat.
Put a tablespoon of meat and some grated cheese along the edge of the tortilla.
Roll up filling in tortilla.
Place in baking pan.
Repeat procedure until pan is full.
If any meat and cheese are left, sprinkle along top of enchiladas.
Pour enchilada sauce over enchiladas until covered.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Lightly oil a griddle and heat to 325° or medium heat.
Ladle potato mixture onto the griddle, flattening it slightly.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on the first side; turn and cook an additional 5 to 8 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and place in crock.
Cover with lime (mix 1 cup of lime to 1 gallon of water).
Soak 12 to 14 hours.
Rinse well and with salt water, soak 4 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Bring to boil the vinegar, sugar and spices (placed in cloth bag).
Pour over cucumbers.
Let soak overnight.
Cook syrup and cucumbers in large pot until cucumbers are clean; pack in hot jars and seal.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: This was usually baked but could be heated on top of stove. Recipe evolved for variety during winters when diets were limited to home grown produce; one of my favorites.

title: mrs. charlie mccraw's coconut cake
directions: Break eggs into bowl; beat well, then add margarine and Crisco.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Then add this and all other ingredients to eggs and Crisco mixture.
Mix well in mixer. Put into pans and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Set aside. Remove crust from bread and tear into pieces.
Place half of torn bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Put 1/2 of the drained sausage over bread, then 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers. Pour egg-milk mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place on baking sheet in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blue cheese spread
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: oriental salad
directions: Run hot water over plain noodles for about 2 minutes.
Mix shredded cabbage, water chestnuts and onions in bowl.
Add plain noodles.
Mix sugar, vinegar and chicken flavor packet from noodles.
Pour over salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve in the serving centers.

title: baked chicken dinner in one pan
directions: Place the vegetables in a roasting pan which has a tight fitting cover and will be large enough to accommodate all of the chicken, too.
Place the chicken halves over the vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; pour all the cream over the chicken. Dot with squares of butter.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until you can pierce the thickest part of the chicken with sharp fork.
Uncover and place under the broiler for 5 minutes or until the chicken is a golden brown.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 4.

title: apple-chocolate cake
directions: Combine the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Combine the oil, vanilla, eggs and milk and add to flour mixture. Stir just until moist, then stir in the remaining ingredients. Grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Pour in mixture. Bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired. Makes 16 servings.

title: aunt may craver's turnip whip
directions: Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Add salt, pepper and turnips, mixing thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold turnip mixture into beaten egg whites.
Add melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Brown onions, butter, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed and mustard.
Slice rolls lengthwise and spread filling on both sides. Lay ham and cheese on top, then wrap in tinfoil until hot.
May be cut with electric knife for individual servings.
Great for a party or shower!

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together, pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool well.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine
in a saucepan, milk and eggs; beat well.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; slowly pour dry ingredients
into	egg
mixture, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Cook
until it thickens.
Take off heat and add vanilla and
butter;
let
cool.
Put
sliced
peaches in the graham cracker
crust.
Poor the cooled filling over peaches. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place first 3 ingredients
in
small
pan and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Mix
together
with
next 4 ingredients. Place in 1 1/2
quart
baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake
at
400° until brown and bubbly on top.

title: no-fail schaum torte
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Beat until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Continue beating until soft peaks.
Add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating all the while until sugar is dissolved and very stiff peaks form, 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in 10-inch buttered pan.
Place in hot oven at 450°.
Close door and turn off heat.
Let stand overnight; do not open door.
Top with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: sour cream chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Melt chocolate and add gradually to mixture while mixing.
Add vanilla.
Combine baking soda and sour cream.
Add quickly to egg-sugar mixture.
Combine until smooth. Sift flour before measuring.
Sift with salt and add 1 cup at a time until just blended.
Do not overmix.
(Batter will be thick and rich.)
Add the 1 cup boiling water and mix until blended. Pour into Bundt pan or other fancy pan which has been greased and powdered with cocoa.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Check for doneness after 1 hour.
Glaze with diluted fudge icing so that it drips down sides, if desired.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove stems and seeds from green peppers.
Rinse and drain on paper towel.
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion, rice and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Stuff green peppers with mixture. Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato juice over stuffed peppers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wiggle pops(diabetic recipe)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add fruit puree.
Stir until well blended and pour into paper cups.
Cover cups with foil. Make slits in centers of foil covers.
Insert popsicle sticks in slits to keep them upright.
Freeze.
Peel off paper; cut and eat. Makes 3 pops.
One pop equals 1/3 fruit.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add all other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients, then add to creamed ingredients.
Add apples and pecans last.
Put in 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350°.
Check after 25 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and salt in large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Stir until chips and marshmallows are melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: apple stuffing
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onions, celery, apples and raisins.
Cook and stir frequently for 5 minutes until softened. Remove from heat; stir in stuffing mix and seasonings.
Add cider to moisten.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
For crisp top, remove cover the last 5 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Add flour, salt and paprika; mix well.
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive to cover.
At this point you can refrigerate or freeze for up to 10 days.
Bake puffs at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 48 appetizers.

title: squeezable stuff("gak")
directions: You will also need paper cups, plastic spoons and plastic plates.

title: ala mary chicken
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Toss dressing well.
Add poultry seasoning.
Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Put 1/2 crumbs on bottom.
Spread chicken over crumbs.
Mix together last four ingredients. Pour all over chicken.
Cover with remaining 1/2 of crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 10.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Mix in saucepan, oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Use greased and floured (or cocoa) Bundt pan.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuit dough very thin (about 1/8 inch thick).
Pare and core apples.
Fill center with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut the biscuit dough in strips and wrap around apples.
Dot the dumplings with butter and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender. Drain; save liquid.
Put vegetables in separate dish.
In the same pan, saute onions in butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add one cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts, 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Boil chicken with the bay leaves, onions and bell pepper until chicken is done.
Add the potatoes (can leave skin on) to the broth from chicken.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add 1/2 cup milk and flour.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups hot milk and both cans of corn.
Cook this about 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Serve with corn bread or Ritz crackers.

title: red and green tomato pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Brush shell with evaporated milk. Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 5 minutes.
Fill shell with tomatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on tomatoes.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix brown sugar, garlic powder and soy sauce.
Spread over chicken wings.

title: french toast
directions: *Slightly dry French bread works best and is firmer.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Score steak on both sides in a diamond pattern.
Brush each side with 1 tablespoon mustard; place in a large shallow dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and marinate 8 hours.
Broil steak 5 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness, basting with remaining marinade.
Slice steak thinly to serve.
Serves 5.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Whip eggs, milk and vanilla together and pour over bread cubes. Cover tightly and chill at least 1 hour or overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with syrup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked, drained broccoli in saucepan with cheese.
Cook on low until cheese melts.
Mix 1 stick margarine and add to mixture.
Melt other stick and add to crackers.
In casserole dish, either alternate layers of crackers and broccoli or add to top and bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: speedy punch
directions: Mix
juice, water and sugar well.
Just before serving add ginger ale and extract.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain kidney and butter beans.
Fry and drain beef, onion and bacon.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Can be mixed a day in advance.

title: chicken cutlets italienne
directions: Slice each chicken cutlet crosswise in chunks.
Cut zucchini into chunks; dice tomatoes and onion.
From lemon, grate peel and squeeze 2 teaspoons juice.
Mix flour, salt and oregano; use to coat cutlets.

title: lemon freeze pie
directions: Chill milk in freezer for 2 hours.
Whip until thick.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Whip all together.
Crumble vanilla wafers for crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Keep in freezer until all eaten.

title: braised venison
directions: Rub venison with salt, pepper and flour. Brown in hot oil, turning frequently. Add hot water. Cover tightly and cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender, adding more water as it evaporates. Add remaining ingredients and cook for approximately 30 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix cooked, diced chicken, onion, soups, milk, green peas, sour cream, half of cheese and 1/2 stick margarine.
Stir well.
Add to cooked noodles.
Mix together.
Top with rest of cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat, onion, pepper and salt.
Drain.
Stir into meat mixture, rice, cheese, tomatoes and hot sauce.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with some shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° until top cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix margarine, poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion together.
Slice party rolls and layer ham and Swiss cheese. Top with mustard sauce.
Heat until warm in oven.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut in half and scoop out meat of avocados.
Chop onion, garlic and tomato into small pieces.
Add ingredients to a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mash together all ingredients and whip until smooth.
Serve with plate of heated tortilla chips, over nachos, with vegetables, etc.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In colander mix zucchini and salt; let drain about 15 minutes. Squeeze out excess liquid.
Mix zucchini, carrot, onion, parsley, egg, flour and pepper.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into 1/2 inch hot oil in skillet.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown ground chuck, onion and garlic.
Add next 8 ingredients, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
In rectangular 1 1/2-quart casserole, put layer of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Romano cheese.
Repeat once and end with grated Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crock-pot mac-n-cheese
directions: Prepare crock-pot with Crisco.
Mix all ingredients except paprika and pepper.
Pour into crock-pot and sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Cook on low 3 hours.

title: ed's snack
directions: Spread Ritz crackers with peanut butter.
Put on one round slice of raw onion.
Put dab of ketchup inside onion slice.

title: red rice
directions: Cut smoked sausage into bite size pieces.
Put into covered baking dish with rice, tomatoes and chopped onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: sally's old fashion bread
directions: Measure about 4 cups flour.
In in yeast, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Scald milk with butter.
Add about a quarter of the milk to the flour mixture; mix well.
Add 1 egg, mix well.
Add more flour, another quarter of milk; stir.
Add second egg, mix well; more flour.
Another quarter of the milk, more flour, last of milk.
Add flour until dough is kneading consistency.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions; stir in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch container, start with a layer of crushed crackers.
Cover with a layer of pudding.
Continue until ingredients are gone.
End with a layer of crackers.
Heat icing in microwave; pour over the top of crackers.
Chill overnight.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Soften cheese and add the other ingredients.
Mix well and serve on your favorite crackers.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Place in large bowl.

title: donna's hawaiian bread
directions: Core out the center of the loaf leaving a thick shell (1-1 1/2 inch).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into loaf.
Wrap complete loaf with foil and bake for 1 hour at 325.
Serve remaining bread on the side in bite size pieces for dipping.
Also tear the shell for dipping.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cooked chicken.
Blend in the cream of chicken soup and milk (heat together).
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on the shredded cheese. Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes or until brown.
If using uncooked chicken, bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon walnuts
directions: Melt butter,
brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Mix and spread out on cookie sheet to harden.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Wash potatoes and place them in a pot, covered with water. Bring to a boil. When the potatoes are soft (after about 45 minutes), drain cool and peel. Using fork or potato masher, mash the potatoes in a large bowl along with the margarine and sugar, combining well. Add the eggs. Stir in the spices, vanilla and milk. Pour into the pie shell. Bake in a 375° for 45 minutes or until the center is firm.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack firmly into an ungreased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut pie(crustless)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan (no crust) and cook at 350° until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in oven.
Take it out and put a big tray under it.

title: sour milk cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Make a hole in center of dry ingredients.
Pour in butter, egg, vanilla and sour milk.
Work in from center out.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for half hour to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Finish filling freezer to "fill" mark with milk.

title: baked beans
directions: Sort and bring beans to boil.
Turn off heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add fresh water.
Bring to boil and add 1/3 picnic ham or other meat.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Remove extra water and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in 300° to 350° oven until a lot of the moisture is gone.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar slowly, then Jell-O; cream well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Slowly add flour mixture (flour, baking powder).
Mix until smooth.
Spritz out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with additional Jell-O.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 14 minutes until lightly golden brown.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add shortening, salt and honey.
Work flours into mixture, kneading well.
Let rise until double.
Shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Make patties.
Fry in slightly greased pan.

title: taters and beef
directions: Peel and cut taters into medium wedges and place in large pot. Crumble beef into taters.
Add onion, salt and pepper to mixture. Cook over medium heat for around 2 hours or until well cooked. Serve with hot corn bread.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix first five ingredients with mixer.
Place one vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake liner.
Fill about 3/4 with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.
Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until tender and remove meat from bones.
Mix flour and water.
Roll out on floured board, cut into 1-inch strips and drop in boiling broth.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle black pepper over the stew.

title: mexican cornbread in a jiffy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix corn muffin mix as directed on Jiffy box, adding pepper, onions and corn.
Pour into an oiled pan and bake for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: biscuit goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, bell pepper and a little garlic.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce and cream of mushroom soup.
Heat on top of stove Cheez Whiz and sour cream, then mix well with hamburger mixture.

title: royal plum pudding
directions: Drain plums, reserving syrup for sauce.
Remove pits and cut plums in pieces.
Prepare gingerbread mix according to directions on package, adding salt and plum pieces.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into well-greased 6 mold Bundt pan.
Bake uncovered at 375° for about 1 hour.
Loosen edges and immediately unmold on serving plate.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large pot.
Drain grease.
Add potatoes, onion and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Turn off heat and mash potatoes in pan coarsely.
Stir in evaporated milk.
(If you like thick potato soup; add instant potato flakes at this time.) Heat to serving temperature and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: walnut pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Blend crushed graham crackers with 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press firmly over bottom and up sides of lightly buttered 9-inch spring-form pan and then chill.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth; add sugars, gradually beating until well mixed.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin pie spice and pumpkin with heavy cream at low speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with walnut topping.
Bake 10 minutes extra. Cool and refrigerate.
Garnish with whipped cream and pecans.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Beat egg slightly and mix with buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Turn out onto floured board and knead until smooth (2 or 3 minutes).
Divide in half and form into 2 round loaves.
Cut a cross, 1/2-inch deep, in top of each round loaf.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: anise toast
directions: Stir baking powder and flour; set aside.
Cream butter with sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add anise and almond extracts; stir in flour mixture and nuts.
Divide dough in thirds; spread in 15-inch long strips on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and slice in 3/4-inch slices.
Turn on sides.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Turn to other side.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes again until light brown.
Makes about 70 bars.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: In saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon quickly onto waxed paper.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomatoes, water and taco mix.
Add cooked rice.
Put in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: mock lobster salad
directions: Cook fish, tomatoes and whole onion until fish is ready.
Pour into colander.
Take out onion and let cool.
Flake fish and cut in celery.
Add flaked fish, tomatoes, celery and salad dressing.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until hot.
Beat egg yolks.
Dip some of the hot mixture into the yolks. Mix together.
Add hot mixture and yolks back into the saucepan (with other mixture).
Continue to cook over medium heat until thickened.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom of bowl.
Add 3 of the bananas, sliced up.
Pour hot mixture into bowl.
Add rest of bananas and more vanilla wafers.

title: second grade candy
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place between 2 sheets of waxed paper and roll with rolling pin. Set aside and let harden.
Cut into squares.

title: ripe tomato chow chow
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until onions get tender.
Put in cans or jars and seal.

title: mini blue cheese rolls
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter and Blue cheese over low heat. Unroll dough and cut each breadstick into 6 pieces; place in a foil-lined 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour cheese mixture over dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until butter is absorbed and rolls are lightly browned.
Carefully lift foil out of pan; place on a serving dish.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoons
directions: Melt butter. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Shape into cocoons.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased dish; cook at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with crushed cheese crackers.

title: zucchini custard pie
directions: Mix together the margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add to zucchini and milk.
Add spices.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°, then at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain well. Combine beef and next 6 ingredients; stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange bacon on top of beans. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and place in large bowl.
Slice onion and pepper; grate carrots.
Place over top of cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar over raw vegetables (do not stir).
Bring vinegar, salad oil, dry mustard, celery seed and salt to boil.
Pour over cabbage while hot (do not stir).
When cool, refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Stir well to blend before serving.
Drain off liquid before serving.
Will keep a week or more in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish and put a layer of pineapple, then cherry pie filling over it.
Then pour cake mix out of box for the layers.
Spread chopped nuts over cake mix and top with slices of butter evenly on the cake mix.
Bake until firm to touch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line bottom with thin sliced beef.
Wrap 1 slice of bacon around 1 boneless chicken breast and place on beef.
Mix sour cream and soup; spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mary i's meat loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Make top with sweet/sour sauce last 10 minutes.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake.

title: chili
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic until the beef loses its redness. Add tomato juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Before adding beans, rinse them good in colander.
The beans should be the last thing to add.
Cook until hot.
Do not overcook.

title: potatoes with herbs
directions: Combine seasonings in bowl.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in nonstick skillet.
Add 1/3 of potatoes, sprinkle little of seasonings, 4 teaspoons melted margarine and 2 tablespoons onions on potatoes.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Uncover, bake 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
When ready, remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: russian mushrooms
directions: Bring to boil the first 7 items.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook.
Remove garlic.
Pour into jar (glass if possible); top with oil.
Place plastic over lid and tighten top. Let sit 6 days before eating.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, just until moist (batter will be lumpy).
Bake 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms a ball when dropped in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and peanut butter and mix well.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour onto wax paper on greased or buttered pan and let cool.
When cool enough, cut into squares.

title: spinach balls(appetizer)
directions: Cook spinach, then squeeze dry and cool. Add stuffing mix, onion, eggs, butter, cheese and seasoning.
Mix all together. Refrigerate several hours.
Mold into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Turn if bottom is getting too brown. Can be frozen.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and put in undrained pineapple. Spread it until evenly distributed.
Spread can of pie filling over the pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Cut butter into patties and put them at even intervals over cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop hawaiian
directions: Coat pork chops with seasoned flour. Brown on both sides in hot oiled skillet. Spread applesauce, pineapple and nutmeg over pork chops.
Cook over low, uncovered, until pork chops are tender, about 45 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mushroom chowder
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms.
Set aside.
In large pot, heat butter and onion and saute until light golden.
Add mushrooms, other vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and water; stir into vegetable mixture.
Add chicken stock and wine. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in cream and heat until hot but do not boil.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top if desired.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: pickled banana peppers
directions: Use gloves to handle peppers.
Wash and drain peppers.
Cut 2 small slits in each pepper.
Dissolve salt in gallon water and pour over peppers.
Let stand 12 to 18 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Mix sugar, horseradish, garlic and 3 cups water in vinegar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Put peppers into jars, pour the liquid over the peppers and seal.
Process in boiling water canner for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thick. Cool and pour over strawberries in "baked" pie shell.

title: nutmeg butterballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Add flour. Mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls and chill.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar and nutmeg.

title: meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and brown. Drain off fat. Mix all together and simmer with meatballs for 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Cook milk, sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla over medium heat until thick.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until cool and thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 2/3 cups or enough for large cake.

title: icebox fruit cake
