directions: Put milk and marshmallows in large boiler and melt over low heat
(never
boil).
Cut
up cherries and mix with pecans and raisins.
Dredge
all
of
these
with your graham cracker meal. Mix
all
together	in
boiler
with melted marshmallow mixture. Put cake mixture in pan lined with waxed paper.
Let set in refrigerator for several days (or weeks) before eating.

title: pumpkin clusters
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add egg; beat well.
Add pumpkin and mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture with vanilla.
Add chocolate chips.

title: mabel's pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg.
Add vinegar and cold water. Stir mixture into the dry ingredients. Divide dough into fourths.
Roll out one piece at a time.
Makes 4 single crusts or 2 double crusts.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, honey, eggs and mandarin peel.
Add mandarin juice and yogurt.
Sift together unbleached flour and soy flour, baking powder, ginger, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Stir in wheat germ, whole wheat flour and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 to 20 minutes longer or until bread tests done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and refrigerate 2 hours.
Mix 2 cups sugar and 1 cup cold vinegar.
Pour mix over pickles.
Put in covered Tupperware or jars.
Keep refrigerated up to 6 months.

title: goody butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients until crumbly and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa. Stir in milk and butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts if desired and put in an 8-inch pan.
Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Spread over batter in pan and then pour 1 3/4 cups boiling water over also!
DO NOT STIR.
Bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: sliced tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and dress with remaining ingredients, which have been blended together.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut and mix.
May be stored for several days.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package, drain and place in bowl. Add butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Spread over the bottom and up the sides of a greased 10-inch deep-dish pie plate. Spoon cottage cheese into crust; set aside.
In skillet, brown beef, onion and red pepper; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spoon over cottage cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pudding pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat for 10 minutes.
Place in 10-inch ungreased tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Let cake cool for 1 hour before taking out of pan.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Season as desired.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Cover last 15 minutes to prevent overbrowning. Makes 2 large casseroles. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: candied cranberries
directions: Cook the sugar, water, soda and salt until it spins a thread. Wash and drain cranberries.
Drop berries in syrup; cook for 10 minutes with lid on.
Leave lid on and remove from fire.
Let sit until cranberries are cold.
Will last for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
In large mixing bowl, break up tuna fish into small pieces.
Add onion, celery and macaroni.
Add mayonnaise to desired texture.
Chill and serve.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients as you would a meat loaf.
Can add salt or pepper to suit taste. Form a handful of mixture around the cheese stick, then wrap with a noodle.
Repeat, using remaining mixture, placing rolls into a greased baking dish. Top with spaghetti sauce. Cover with oil and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: italian sweet cream cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add egg yolks, flour, soda, buttermilk, vanilla, coconut and pecans; mix.
Gently fold in 5 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs singly, beating after each one.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven and bake at 325° for 90 minutes or until done.

title: red candied apples
directions: Place all ingredients except apples, in a heavy bottomed pan; bring to hard crack on candy thermometer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and dip apples immediately.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a 9-inch round dish.
Mix brown sugar, oatmeal, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut in butter with a pastry blender. Spread evenly over apples.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes. Topping becomes crisper after standing awhile.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar together.
Then add 7-Up and pineapple juice.
Chill and serve.

title: jalapeno corn bread(fast and simple)
directions: Mince fine onion and jalapeno peppers (1 pepper for mild, 2 peppers medium and 3 peppers hot! hot! hot!).
Mix all together muffin mix, tomato juice, egg, peppers, onion and garlic (at least 1 teaspoon).
If mixture seems too thick, add small amount of tomato juice.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: alaskan salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and sugar.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Whip the cream; add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix this with the first part.
Freeze at least 6 hours in a 12 x 7-inch Pyrex dish.
Can be kept for a long period of time.

title: easy lemon cake
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Split cake and put topping on bottom half.
Put cake together and frost.
Put extra frosting in the hole.
Put in freezer.
Serve right out of the freezer.
Enjoy!

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks, milk and lemon juice. Pour into crust.
In bowl beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soft peaks, add sugar and continue to beat until stiff.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix melted oleo, 1 egg and cake mix.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over dough.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cake will fall.

title: individual caramel flan
directions: To caramelize sugar, in a heavy 8-inch skillet cook 1/3 cup sugar over medium-heat until sugar begins to melt, shaking the skillet occasionally to heat the sugar evenly. Do not stir. Once the sugar starts to melt, reduce heat to low. Cook about 5 minutes more or until all the sugar is melted and golden, stirring as needed with a wooden spoon. Immediately divide the caramelized sugar among 4 (6-oz.) custard cups; tilt custard cups to coat bottoms evenly. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla in a medium bowl with a wire whisk.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle chocolate chunks over bottom of pie crust.
Pour pecan mixture into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from center comes out with little bits of filling attached.
Cool 2 hours on wire rack.

title: halibut beer bits
directions: Cut halibut into 2-inch chunks.
Mix pancake mix with beer. Dip both sides of halibut in flour, then into batter and then into hot oil.
Fry about 8 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Boil noodles, until tender.
Layer noodles, sauce, cheese until three or four layers.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: georgia fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in a glass bowl and pour buttermilk over and soak for 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix dry ingredients and dust chicken in it.
Dip chicken in egg, then flour mixture, then bread crumbs. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the cornflakes.
Melt the margarine before mixing with other ingredients (soup doesn't need to be heated).
Put into a 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Crumble cornflakes by hand and spread across top of casserole, approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour. Take foil off of casserole and continue baking for approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until cornflakes are a golden brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: super royal fans
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Work in butter with fingers until mixture resembles pastry.
Divide dough into 4 parts; roll each part into 6-inch rounds.
Cut each round into 6; mark with back of knife like a fan.
Beat egg yolk slightly; add water.
Brush fans with egg mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in moderate oven (375°).
Yields 24 fans.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gina's favorite truffles
directions: Heat cream and butter over medium heat.
Bring to boil. Remove.
Stir in chocolate and liqueur or brandy until chocolate melts.
Refrigerate mixture until you can shape.
Roll into balls. Roll in confectioners sugar or cocoa.
Put on a wax paper lined pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar; let stand for 1/2 hour.
Add egg, flour, salt and soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Mix tuna, macaroni, green pepper, olives, lima beans, eggs, dill pickles and peanuts.

title: lemon air pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 or 10-inch pie pan (10-inch is best).
Put everything into a blender; cover and blend on high speed for about one minute.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until firm in the center.
Add 1/4 cup of lemon juice or 2 tablespoons cocoa for variety.
I told you you would like it!

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix milk, water, sugar, cocoa, flour, cornstarch and 3 egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter in large skillet or kettle and brown meat and onion.
Stir in next 7 ingredients; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine flour and milk.
Stir into soup and boil.
Add remaining flour and heat, stirring frequently.
Heat, but don't allow to boil.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover hash browns with water.
Salt and pepper to taste and add onion salt, if desired.
Boil until tender, about 10 minutes. Do not drain.
Add soups and Velveeta and simmer until all melted together.
May use cream of chicken soup instead of mushroom.
(I think mushroom is better.)

title: easy but good lasagna
directions: Mix browned hamburger with spaghetti sauce.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with sauce.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Pour 1 cup water around edges.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cook noodles before adding to pan.
Place in pan, uncooked, and layer as indicated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 of the butter.
Combine all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with stuffing mix. Pour rest of butter over stuffing mix.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Place 1/2 stick of butter in pan and melt in oven.
Cut the other 1/2 stick butter into the flour.
Mix until resembles coarse meal.
Mix in sugar and baking powder.
Mix in buttermilk.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead dough lightly.
Pat out dough and cut into biscuits.
Coat each biscuit on both sides with melted butter in the pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned at 450°.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix with 1 (16 ounce) can of baked beans, simmer and serve.

title: scripture cake
directions: President Madison's wife, Dolly, was a good cook.
She was also a very religious woman.
As was the custom in those days, she did not give out her recipes.
After repeated requests for this cake recipe, Mrs. Madison prepared it in this manner to make it necessary to read the Bible to complete the cake.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut your steak into bite size pieces (the steak does not have to be an expensive cut).
Take your water chestnuts (sliced) and drain them.
Cut bacon into thirds or halves (enough to wrap around steak).
Wrap bacon around steak and a slice of water chestnut. Secure with a toothpick.
Place in a bowl and pour soy sauce over steak.
Cover and marinate overnight.
(I prefer low sodium soy sauce; it makes the appetizer less salty.)
Cook in broiler pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve alone or with sweet and sour sauce.

title: ginger crinkles cookies
directions: We like these, so double the recipe.
Chill in refrigerator. Make into balls (about walnut size or smaller).
Roll in white sugar.
Place far apart on a cookie pan.
Cool some before removing them.
Keep closed in tight container for soft cookies.

title: busy day lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain any excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt, oregano and thyme; mix thoroughly and bring to a boil.
Stir in uncooked noodles; reduce heat, cover and simmer gently for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle the shredded Mozzarella cheese on top and heat until cheese melts.
Enjoy!

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
In large bowl toss noodles with cottage cheese, mozzarella and parmesan cheeses. In 2 qt. oblong pan spoon enough sauces to cover bottom of pan. Layer noodles and sauce.
Put sauce on top and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese on top.

title: punch
directions: Dilute lemonade and orange juice.
Then add 1 can Hawaiian juice and 1 bottle of ginger ale at a time.
Add ice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat two 8 inch cake pans with cooking spray. In a large bowl with an electric beater on medium speed, beat the cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil, and eggs until smooth. Stir in the pineapple then pour the batter into pans, dividing equally. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Allow to cool for 15 minutes, then invert onto wire racks to cool completely.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Blend sugar, butter, flour and salt until creamy.
Add well-beaten eggs, vanilla and buttermilk last.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain water and put noodles in a buttered dish.
Add tuna and chopped onion; mix with noodles.
Spread soup on top.
Pour cream over all.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat the milk and the cardamom, and add half the sugar.
When the sugar is dissolved, remove the milk from the heat.
Whisk the eggs and egg yolks with the remaining sugar until light and rib-bony.
Combine the milk with the eggs, stirring well to prevent the eggs from cooking prematurely.
Combine the sweet potatoes and honey.
Toss the bread and the sweet potato mixture, mixing well.
Add the milk mixture, and let the bread soak up the milk.
Stir, and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
If desired, top with whipped cream and/or drizzle with additional honey.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion to desired taste until tender and drain.
Add milk, water and soup until creamy on low heat.
Add butter until melted on low heat.
Stir often.
Add salt and pepper to season.
Add 1/2 pkg.
Velveeta cheese 5 - 10 minutes prior to serving after soup is removed from heat.
Cheese will melt with the lid on the pot.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: stale bread cookies
directions: Cut slices of bread in fine strips.
Dip strips into condensed milk.
Drain and roll in shredded coconut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: squeaky door cake(german chocolate caramel cake)
directions: Bake German chocolate cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan. After removing from oven, poke holes generously with end of wooden spoon and pour a can of condensed milk over it.
Then top the cake with Mrs. Richardson's topping.
Place in refrigerator.
When cake is completely cool spread Cool Whip over top of cake and sprinkle nuts or pecans over top.
Store in refrigerator and watch your diet.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Dust veal lightly with flour mixture.
Brown meat slowly in hot oil.
Remove from skillet and cook until tender but not brown.
Add all other ingredients to the skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes; stir occasionally. Arrange the veal on hot buttered noodles and top with the sauce from the skillet.

title: deer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into rolls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 170° for 8 hours, turning every 2 hours.
Do not wrap during baking.
Sausage will form its own skin.
Cool, wrap and freeze.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla until creamy.
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Layer pineapple, then bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on bananas and decorate with cherries and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Soften yeast in cool milk.
Add salt, shortening, sugar and water.
Add flour a little at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat until smooth.
Cover with warm cloth and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll to about 1/3-inch thick.
Cut in rounds with small glass and put a little butter on.
Then fold over. Press edges together.
Put on well-oiled baking sheets.
Cover and let rise until triples bulk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on high rack.
Makes quite a lot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain on paper towels and cool.
Put into mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into well greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until set and lightly browned on top.
May be used for brunch or light supper.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut meat into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in hot shortening, drain.
Add tomato sauce, onion slices, garlic salt, beef-flavored base, Worcestershire sauce, salt and dash of pepper to browned meat.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 50 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Cook, covered, until pepper is tender (6 to 8 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients with rice. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
9 to 10 servings.

title: 7-up salad
directions: In a bowl, mix cream cheese; add slowly the bottle of 7-Up and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix jello, sugar, hot water and pineapple.
Mix together and chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 1 1/2 quart baking dish and bake in a moderate oven until browned.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Mix well beaten eggs with remaining ingredients and add to drained ground beef.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until well done.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in top of double boiler. Mix in peanuts and noodles. Stir well and drop by teaspoons. Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Make sure shrimp is cleaned well.
If the shrimp are large, cut in half.
Chop egg and add to shrimp in large bowl.
Add celery, olives and onions.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Mix in mustard and mix gently.
You may add a little cooked rice if you don't have enough shrimp.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled. Serves 4.

title: spiced coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, dissolve 1 tablespoon of mix per cup of hot water.

title: marinated beef slices
directions: Marinate beef in lemon juice for 10 minutes. While meat is marinating, heat oil in large skillet; add fresh mushrooms, onions and green pepper. Cook until tender. Remove vegetables from skillet and keep warm. Drain meat, reserving lemon juice marinade. Place meat slices in skillet and brown. Return vegetables to skillet. Add reserved lemon juice and pepper. Heat through. Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: dorothy's apple pie filling
directions: In large saucepan blend first 4 ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir in 10 cups water; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice, pack apples into hot jars, leaving 1 inch headspace to help distribute syrup.
Process in cold packer 15 minutes for pints and 20 minutes for quarts.
Makes 6 quarts. Bake pie at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick waffles
directions: Beat whole eggs in a bowl until thick.
Beat in milk and melted butter. Combine remaining ingredients.
Sift into egg mixture and beat well.
Bake and serve with desired topping.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours or overnight. Will keep 2 weeks.

title: zippy turkey and mac
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.

title: jello divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and boil slowly until it will form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg whites fairly stiff.
Sprinkle jello over them and beat until stiff. Pour syrup over the whites. Mix and add nuts.
Beat until candy is ready to drop from a spoon onto a greased pan.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes on high speed. You can make a sheet cake out of the mixture or you can cook in 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until it springs back at touch.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Remove chicken from bones, skin and cut into cubes.
Combine chicken and remaining ingredients with exception of corn flakes and cheese.
Let stand for an hour and taste to see if additional salt is needed.
Spoon into a buttered 2-quart baking dish*.
Top with crumb/cheese mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Place sugar and syrup together in large pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir thoroughly. Add cereal.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam or line with buttered waxed paper.
Press cereal mixture into pan.
After the mixture has cooled, melt together the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over cereal mixture and cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Divide in 1/2.
In first half, add 1 stick butter and 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fantasy fudge(microwave)
directions: Easy in the microwave:
Melt margarine in a 4-quart bowl on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well. Microwave on High for 5 minutes, until mixture begins to boil; stir after 3 minutes.
Mix well.
Scrape bowl.
Microwave for 5 1/2 minutes; stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add pineapple, bananas, and walnuts.
Bake 350 for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Cool.
I cook in a bundt pan.

title: sweet rye bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup water; set aside.
Combine the next 6 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cool to lukewarm. Combine soda and cold water.
Add this to milk mixture.
It will bubble up.
Put all in large bowl and add remaining ingredients. Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down and let rest 30 minutes.
Divide in two parts.
Form into loaves and place in well-greased pans.
Cover and let rise until light, about one hour.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: old fashion sweet potato pone
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, grated potatoes, spices, milk and salt.
Stir in syrup and grated rind.
Mix all together well and pour into well buttered casserole dish.
Bake in a 325° oven about 1 hour or until set.
Cool and cut into pieces like a cake.

title: swiss pie
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, saving drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion in drippings until tender, but not brown; drain.
Blend in sour cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add bacon and cheese.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs in hot spaghetti noodles. Press mixture into 10-inch pie plate to form crust.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Mix meat and spaghetti sauce together.
Pour over cottage cheese. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Place in 1-quart baking dish.
May be frozen at this point.
If frozen, thaw slightly and top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pecan bars
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir until moistened. Pat into bottom of a greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs lightly.
Beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour over mixture in pan, spreading evenly.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Yield:
3 to 4 dozen.

title: icebox oatmeal crisp cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients. Add oatmeal and nuts. Mix well. Roll in wax paper in two slender round rolls and chill overnight. Then cut into thin round pieces and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts together.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and cool. Mix together cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth and spread on crust.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until thick and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top before serving.

title: ceramic league cake
directions: Blend with fork as you would for piecrust.
Spread and pat gently into 9 x 13 pan.
Do not pack down.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chilli cups
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in ham, drained chilies and grated cheese.
Open biscuits and flatten.
Cut biscuits in half and mold to small cupcake tins.
Fill with 1 teaspoon of filling.
Bake Chillie Cups for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove and place on a dish.

title: best yet cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, butter and cream of tartar together for 5 minutes. Stir in soda.
Add popcorn and peanuts.
Mix thoroughly and spread on 2 slightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 200° for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar, shortening, egg and salt.
Put yeast, 1/2 tablespoon sugar and warm water in big bowl and let stand for 20 minutes.
To yeast mixture, add 2 cups warm water and mix well. Then add first mixture.
Mix together and add 6 to 8 cups flour. Knead well.
Put in greased bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk. Knead again and put into loaf or 6 coffee cans.
Let rise.
Pour cans 1/3 full.
Grease cans or loaf pans.
Bake at 375°.

title: yankee muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine apples and sugar.
Gently fold in cranberries, carrots and nuts.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixing bowl.
Mix well to moisten.
Combine eggs and oil.
Stir into apple mixture.
Fill 18 greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: springtime sautéed spinach
directions: Heat Italian dressing in large deep skillet or Dutch oven on medium heat.
Add garlic; cook and stir 1 minute, or until tender. Add spinach leaves; cover and cook an additional 4 to 6 minutes, or until spinach is wilted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Makes 4 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: german soft pretzels
directions: In a bowl dissolve yeast in water. Add 1-1/2 cups of the flour, oil and sugar. Beat for about 3 minutes to make a smooth batter. Gradually stir in enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn out onto a floured board and knead until smooth and satiny (about 5 minutes). Add flour as needed to prevent sticking. Place dough in a greased bowl and turn over to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 1 hour). Punch down dough. Turn out onto a floured board and divide into 12 pieces. Shape each into a smooth ball by gently kneading. Then roll each into a smooth rope (about 18 inches long) and twist into a pretzel shape. Place slightly apart on a greased baking sheet turning loose ends underneath. Let rise uncovered until puffy (about 25 minutes). Meanwhile in a 3-quart stainless steel or enameled pan (not aluminum) bring baking soda water to a boil. Adjust heat to keep water boiling gently. With a slotted spatula, lower one pretzel at a time into pan. Let simmer for 10 seconds on each side, then lift from water, drain briefly on spatula, and place on baking sheet. Let dry briefly; then sprinkle with coarse salt and let stand, uncovered, until all have simmered.

title: microwave roux
directions: Use a 4-cup microwave cup.
Mix flour and oil.
Microwave 6 minutes. Stir in all chopped vegetables, except green onions. Microwave on High 3 minutes. Add green onions.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.

title: cousin glen's hamburger corn bake
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine all in a 2 1/2-quart casserole with 3 cups medium cooked noodles.
Top all with 1 cup bread crumbs (mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter if desired).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put melted margarine in baking dish.
Add rice, broccoli and chicken.
Stir together soup, water and milk and envelope of soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 3/4 hours at 325°.

title: red lobster biscuits (cheese biscuits)
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until dough forms into small ball. Beat 30 seconds on high speed of mixer (optional). Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush on top. Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: casserole supreme
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain well.
Add tomato soup, egg noodles, corn, water and salt and pepper.
Bring all to boil in an iron skillet.
Cover and simmer until noodles are done. Transfer to casserole dish and top with cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: grandmother's cherry pudding
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter.
Mix dry	ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Heat
3/4	cup sugar
and cherries.	 Put
batter
in baking dish
and
pour cherries over the top.
Bake at 350°.
Batter will rise to the top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sour cream, soup, onion and water chestnuts.
Melt margarine and pour 1/2 in large baking dish.
Spread over bottom. Sprinkle 1/2 of dressing mix on top of butter.
Pour in squash mixture.
Layer with remaining dressing mix and then remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: congress tarts
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and egg.
Add the flour, milk, baking powder, salt and vanilla and mix until smooth.
Line muffin tins with a pie pastry.
Put in 1 teaspoon strawberry or other jam. Put some of the cake batter on top and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Combine oleo and sugar and mix well.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Adjust time if making smaller loaves.
Mini loaves make great homemade Christmas gifts for teachers, etc.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients, stirring frequently, until margarine is melted.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Place chicken in large skillet; add water to cover.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear when pierced with a fork.
Drain and cut into small, bite-size pieces when cool enough to handle.
Set aside.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Drain pineapple and save syrup.
In skillet, melt oleo and add onion and green pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup boiling water.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in a mixture of chopped nuts and parsley.
Chill until served.

title: hard rock cafe baked potato soup
directions: Chop bacon and reserve.
Cook onions in drippings over medium-high heat about 3 minutes.

Add flour, stirring to prevent lumps, 3 to 5 minutes, until mixture just starts to turn golden. Add chicken stock, gradually, stirring until liquid thickens. Reduce heat to simmer and add potatoes, cream, chopped bacon, parsley, garlic, basil, salt, Tabasco sauce and black pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Do not allow to boil.
Add grated cheese and green onions. Heat until cheese melts smoothly. Makes 2 quarts, about 8 servings.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix cooked rice and mushroom soup.
Add onion, celery and uncooked, thawed broccoli. Stir in cheese.
Add additional cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion until brown.
Add chicken stock and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add creamed corn (can use 1 can creamed corn and 1 can kernel corn), salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Use flour and milk to thicken.
Add half and half.
Heat, but do not boil.
Delicious!

title: annie's tofu loaf
directions: Squeeze excess water out of tofu and mash in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
(Use butter or margarine to grease pan.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Crust:
Cream together brown sugar, butter and sugar.
Add egg, soda, vanilla, salt and peanut butter.
Mix in flour and oats.
Put onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or light brown. Cool for 5 minutes.

title: apple roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with Pam.
Line with wax paper and spray again.
Spread applesauce evenly over pan and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thick and light.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg whites; stir in vanilla.
Spread evenly over applesauce. Bake 15 to 18 minutes until golden.
Let set 5 minutes.
Turn apple side up on a paper towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Remove waxed paper and crusty edges.
Roll lengthwise and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 10 servings with 130 calories and .2 gram fat per serving.

title: easy home-cooked cheese
directions: Melt oleo; add cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring until melted.
Combine milk and flour and mix until smooth.
Add to cheese mixture and simmer until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add caraway seed to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: yum yum squares
directions: Cream together all ingredients but chocolate chips.
Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over batter.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1 cup brown sugar, firmly packed, and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread over chocolate chips and batter.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.

In medium saucepan, gradually stir reserved beet liquid into cornstarch to make a smooth mixture. Add orange marmalade, vinegar and salt. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Add butter and stir until melted.
Add beets and stir gently over low heat until evenly glazed and heated through. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: almost better than sex cake
directions: Combine everything except chocolate chips and pecans in a bowl.
Beat only until mixture is combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour batter into a 10-inch Bundt pan, greased and coated with flour.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until it loses redness; drain fat. Stir in water, uncooked macaroni, onion, peppers, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until macaroni is transparent.
Add tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes with lid off.

title: fruit dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in microwave for 45 seconds or until soft. Beat with other ingredients.
Serve with strawberries, bananas, apples, etc.
Can add juice from orange to dip mixture if desired.

title: cheese blintzes(cinnamon roll-ups)
directions: Remove crust from bread and flatten each slice with a rolling pin. Mix together cream cheese, flavorings and egg yolk. Spread approximately 1 heaping teaspoon of the mixture per slice of bread.
Roll the bread up as a jelly roll and cut into three pieces.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Wash chicken pieces.
Coat with flour and salt.
Brown in 1/2 cup hot shortening.
As pieces brown, arrange in a baking dish.
Saute onion and melted butter in a saucepot until clear.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish and bake 1 hour or until tender.

title: mediterranean linguine(it's easy and delicious!)
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions, omitting salt and oil. Meanwhile, coat a large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot. Add mushrooms, peppers and garlic; cook until vegetables are tender. Add artichokes, dressing, olives and parsley; cook, stirring occasionally until heated through, about 3 minutes. Combine vegetable mixture with linguine; toss well. Transfer mixture to serving dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Serve immediately. Makes 11 servings.

title: apple cheese dessert
directions: Put apples in dish.
Mix water and cinnamon.
Pour over apples.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in bowl and pour over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and chill.
Add pudding to 3 cups juice and cook until a good boil.
Cool and mix with chilled fruit.
Refrigerate and cool.
Add bananas (just before serving) and serve.

title: anna's green peas
directions: Heat peas in microwave 10 minutes. Add cheese, water chestnuts, pimientos and butter. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and slice lengthwise.
Put yolks in medium size bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Mix with mixer until smooth. Spoon into the egg white halves and place on serving platter. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef (season with salt and pepper to taste).
Strain meat and set aside.
Dice onion and pour water off of mushrooms. You can use the same skillet to melt butter and brown the onion and mushrooms.
After you have done this, return the ground beef to the skillet and reheat.

title: ground turkey joes(diet)
directions: Brown turkey in Teflon skillet.
Add ingredients and simmer.

title: harry's french bread #2
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar and salt.
Put 1 cup flour in food processor.
Add yeast mixture and blend.
Add oil and flour, 1 cup at a time.
Process until ball is formed.
Remove to a floured counter and knead just until smooth.
Shape into 2 balls and let rise for 10 minutes.
Roll into a 9 x 12-inch rectangle, then roll up jelly roll style and put onto a baking sheet that has been greased and dusted with corn meal.
Make 4 or 5 diagonal cuts on top with sharp knife.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. When done, brush with melted butter.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill at least one hour.
Cook pasta al dente and drain well.
Toss hot pasta with cold marinated tomatoes and serve or cover and chill.
When serving, sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan.

title: peter paul cake
directions: Devil's Food or chocolate cake mix and cook per directions on box.
Cook in large pan, 18 x 12-inch.

title: jalapeno bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until steaming.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12 Pyrex dish while oven preheats to 350°. Mix milk, flour and sugar. Then add pie filling (apple, cherry, blueberry) and pour into greased dish. Cook until firm and lightly browned on top (about 30 minutes). Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly dust with flour one (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream oil, eggs and sugars together.
Sift dry ingredients and add creamed mixture.
Fold in oatmeal and raisins. Bake 30 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine and mix well enough for 2 deep dish pizzas.

title: sweet potato shoo-fly
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until cooked.
Mash with mixer, adding milk, butter, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Add chopped pecans, chopped fine.
Add brown sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Continue mixing until all ingredients are mixed well.
Place into a baking dish; place marshmallows on top.
Bake until marshmallows are browned at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour 1 can Hawaiian Punch into ring mold; freeze. Mix remaining Hawaiian Punch and remaining ingredients.
Add frozen ring.
Serve.
Serves 45.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place wings, margarine and 3 cups water in stockpot.
Bring to a boil.
Cook on medium heat for 35 minutes until chicken is done. Add remaining ingredients to chicken and broth.
Cook over low heat for about 30 minutes until noodles are soft.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg. Add remaining ingredients in order listed and beat until smooth.
Yields 10 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar together; add eggs and sour milk and beat well.
Mix spices and soda with flour and add to mix.
Mix well and add oatmeal and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Empty contents of macaroni and cheese package (including cheese packet) into casserole dish.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until browned slightly on top and bubbly.

title: missionary icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until it boils, constantly stirring.
Let cool completely and add other ingredients and beat mixture about 5 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Add
onion, garlic and celery to cooking oil and brown. Add salt, lemon juice (or vinegar), mustard, sugars, Tabasco, pepper, Worcestershire and tomato soup.
Cook on low fire for 10
to
15 minutes.
Makes
2	to
3 pints.
May be stored in freezer for unlimited time.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: ham macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; drain and rinse with cold water.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni with next 5 ingredients. Pour on Italian dressing; toss gently.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place on lettuce leaves.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well.
Add vanilla, walnuts, eggs and oil.
Mix together.
Add apples.
Bake in a tube pan, greased and floured for 1 hour at 350°.

title: b.s.'s teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix together teriyaki, water, brown sugar, pineapple, garlic powder, ginger powder and pepper.
Stir ingredients in large pot until brown sugar is dissolved.
Add chicken to sauce.
Cook on stove top until done.
Approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Take sauce from chicken after cooking and thicken with flour or cornstarch to make an excellent gravy for rice or potatoes.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Prepare mix as directed on package for pie filling except using 1 cup milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Combine strawberries and sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To each serving, add strawberry mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zingy potato salad
directions: Marinate warm potatoes in French dressing 1 hour in a large bowl.
Combine onion, parsley, pickles, pimiento, mustard, salt and pepper.
Gently fold in sour cream. Add potatoes, celery and eggs.
Toss lightly.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors. Yields 6 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Brown the butter and add to the potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing after each.
Put in greased baking dish and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Place marshmallows on top.
Return to oven and brown lightly.

title: chicken delightful
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with 1/2 stuffing mix.
Heat oleo in broth; pour over stuffing.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Spoon into pan.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over mix in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. When ready to cook, spread soup and remaining stuffing over mix in pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chewy cocoa brownies
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar (gradually add sugar).
Add eggs and blend.
Add sifted dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 325°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream the oleo.
Add sugar; gradually cream until light and fluffy.
Add 2 tablespoons of milk, then eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with remaining milk.
Fold in bananas, chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine minced shrimp, mayonnaise and onions together.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight for best flavor.
Serve with your choice of crackers.
(Easy to double.) Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chewy brownies(from 100% pleasure)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 8-inch square baking pan with aluminum foil, overlapping at two ends by 1 1/2 inches.
Spray foil with nonstick spray.
Sift together first 4 ingredients onto wax paper.

Combine chocolate and margarine in saucepan over lowest heat, stirring frequently, until just melted and smooth. Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup, water and vanilla until well blended.

title: beef 'n cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
After 25 minutes check, may need to add a little extra water.

title: jubilee jumbles cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening and sugar, add eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in.
Blend in nuts.
CHILL ONE HOUR.
Heat oven to 375 degrees; drop rounded tablespoonful of dough 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes until delicately brown. While warm frost, garnish with nuts.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a deep, 1-quart, heat-resistant (microwave-safe) casserole, combine all ingredients.
Heat, uncovered, on High in microwave oven for 8 minutes or until the mixture boils.
Stir mixture occasionally during last 3 minutes of cooking time.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Serve either hot or chilled.
Serves 6.

title: dorothy's pressure pot country style steak
directions: Dredge cubed steak in flour and fry in small amount of oil in pressure pot, frying 2 or 3 pieces at a time.
After all meat has been browned, put back into pot.
Sprinkle with about 5 tablespoons flour.
Pour on enough water to cover; add onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 30 minutes after control jiggles on 10 pounds of pressure.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Grease baking sheet; set aside.
Combine sugar and water. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until water evaporates and nuts are sugary (approximately 12 minutes).
Spread nuts on sheet, separating them.
Let stand until cool.
Flavors can be added. Makes 1 pound.

title: cocktail smoky links
directions: Combine chili sauce and grape jelly in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture begins to boil. Add sausage; cook an additional 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Serve with wooden picks.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: aunt frances's spice tea
directions: Simmer all ingredients on stove. Remove spices when it suits your taste.

title: german red cabbage
directions: In large kettle, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boiling over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered and stirring occasionally, 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until most of the liquid is absorbed and cabbage is tender.
Thicken at end with a bit of flour sprinkled over the cabbage and stirred in.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Set oven for 375°.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Add salt to egg yolks; beat until thick.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk, butter or margarine and lemon juice; blend well.
Fold in coconut and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sweet crispy pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice 3/4 inch thick.
Seed cucumbers with a doughnut cutter.
Soak cucumbers overnight in lime water (2 cups builders lime to 2 gallons of water).
Rinse very well.
Cover with ice water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Cover with vinegar, sugar spice mix and allow to stand overnight.
Bring to a boil and cook 35 minutes. Jar and seal.
Makes 6-7 pints.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions and celery
in margarine until tender.
Thaw broccoli.
Mix these ingredients well.
Add cheese, water chestnuts, rice and mushroom soup.
Bake in 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: toddle house chocolate pie
directions: Put sugar, flour and cocoa (in this order) in saucepan; stir to mix.
Add milk gradually, stirring to dissolve sugar; add egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
This will get really thick.
Stir in butter and then add vanilla, stirring to smooth.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add next 4.
Sift remaining dry ingredients into the mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased tube pan.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until just done.
Grate cheese.
Drain macaroni and add the cheese while hot (save some to sprinkle on top).
Stir in margarine and milk.
Mix well.
Add more milk if needed to make creamy.
Bake in greased casserole dish until bubbly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into thick slices.
Boil carrots in water 10 minutes, or until tender, taking care not to overcook. Drain well and place in bowl with garlic, salt, pepper, oil, vinegar and oregano; stir and mix well.
Let stand in marinade 12 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, unmold on large serving plate.
Surround with pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges or any fruit combination.
Place fruit in the center, too.

title: mint dazzler
directions: Blend vanilla wafers or graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the powdered sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon over crumbs in pan.
Refrigerate.
Whip the cream (or use Cool Whip); gently fold in the marshmallows.
Spread carefully over the chocolate layer.
Sprinkle crushed mints over the top.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.
Cut into squares and serve.
Very refreshing.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Serve in a hollowed out rye or pumpernickel round bread.
Cut bread in bite size pieces.
Place around outside of loaf.
This is great as a veggie dip, too.

title: eight course dinner
directions: Place all raw items in casserole in order given.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: carrot relish or copper pennies
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour the hot marinade over the carrots, onion and pepper. Chill.
Will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: grandma's german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
When done, peel and slice.
Remove bacon from pan; put on top of sliced potatoes.
Cook 1 large onion in bacon fat.
Add flour, salt, pepper, 1 cup of water, sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Heat to the boiling point.
Keep stirring until thick.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Let stand 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Enough for 4 to 6 people.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix together and add 2 tablespoons red lemon-lemon juice.
Kids love it.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Spray long Pyrex dish with Pam.
Place raw, salted chicken in dish.
Sprinkle chopped onion on chicken.
Mix milk with soup; pour over chicken.
Dot with margarine, or squeeze margarine over chicken in several places.
Cover with foil; bake in slow oven (200°) for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
(Perfect for Sundays.
Mine goes in around 9:00 and is done when I get home around 12:30.)
Brown under broiler just before serving.
You need no extra gravy for rice.

title: macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together milk and coconut; add vanilla and stir well.
Stir in lemon peel.
Put egg whites into bowl.
Beat whites with electric mixer on low until frothy.
Add salt and beat on high until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into coconut mixture.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool on flat surface.
Repeat until all batter is cooked.

title: north carolina pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Lightly beat egg yolks.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add flour, flavoring and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, salt, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Scramble and brown hamburger and onion.
When mixture is done, add seasonings and Ragu sauce.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Cook the lasagna noodles according to package directions.
When noodles are done, layer in a baking dish, then a layer of the hamburger mixture and a layer of the Mozzarella cheese (add cottage cheese if you want).
Bake in a 350° oven until the cheese bubbles.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Bring butter and cream cheese to room temperature.
Cream butter and cream cheese together, slowly adding sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla until blended.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Will brown lightly around bottom and lightly on top.
Then they are firmly set.

title: tea cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl; add vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown on edge.

title: pina colada wedges
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and rum until smooth. Fold in 2 cups nondairy whipped topping, pineapple juice and 2 cups coconut. Spread mixture in 8-inch square pan. Spread remaining nondairy whipped topping on top. Freeze 2 hours. Garnish with coconut, cherries and pineapple.

title: grilled turkey or chicken steaks
directions: Tenderize boneless turkey or chicken breasts.
Prepare marinade with the ingredients listed previously.
Marinate meat for a few hours or overnight.
Place foil on charcoal grill and grill meat approximately 10 minutes on each side (or until no longer pink).

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix all together in large plastic container and freeze at least 1 day before you use it.
Put ice in glass and 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of slush and fill glass with 7-Up.

title: peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with peaches.
Pour into single unbaked crust.
Pour cream over.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Reduce to 300° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and spices together and combine with margarine mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, carrots, raisins and nuts. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 minutes at 350°.

title: texas cake
directions: Melt the butter, water and cocoa.
Add all remaining ingredients fast.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on large cookie sheet.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix
sugar and eggs; add flour, nuts, fruit and flavorings. Mix
well.	Press
into
greased
tube
pan.
Bake	15 minutes at 300°, then 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugars.
Add the beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Stir in the vanilla; beat in the peanut butter.
Mix the flour with the baking soda and salt.
Stir the flour mixture into the batter.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar and place 2 inches apart on baking sheets.
Squash with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turkish olive salad
directions: Slice the tomatoes, ripe olives and green olives. Chop the parsley. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; add lemon juice to coat. Cover and place in refrigerator for 2 hours. Serve as side dish for chicken or steak or use as a garnish for hamburgers.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Grease and sugar 1 loaf pan and 4 or 5 mini loaf pans.
Divide batter evenly and fill about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: microwave rice krispie treats
directions: Microwave
butter
add marshmallows on Full power for 2 minutes
in a large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine ingredients. Cook
on
High
for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer.
Add cereal and coconut.
Mix
until
well	coated	and
spread
out on cookie sheets. Cheerios can be substituted for Rice Krispies.

title: peach yum yum pie
directions: Mix together and spread in 13 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: best divinity
directions: Bring to a rolling boil in a deep pan the sugar, syrup and water. Cover and time for 3 minutes. Uncover and cook to soft ball. Pour in 2 stiff beaten egg whites. Beat until almost cool. Add nuts, salt and vanilla. Drop on wax paper.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spice drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Combine milk and molasses.
Add to shortening mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Drop from teaspoon.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Stir ingredients well.
Bake in 1-quart casserole dish at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir in the cup of boiling water, sugar and add the lemon and pineapple with juice. Chill until firm.
Make the Dream Whip according to directions on box.
Fold into chilled pineapple.
Use low speed of mixer.
Slice cake into thin slices.
Alternate layers of cake and mixture.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: potatoes by bettye
directions: In a deep casserole dish, put 1/2 stick of margarine.
Layer in this order: potatoes, onion and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Put salt and pepper between each layer.

title: make-ahead french spaghetti
directions: Fry onion in 1/2 cup margarine until translucent.
Add tomatoes, stirring to break up.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze out liquid or let thaw and drain.
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze or refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
May also freeze after cooking.

title: vegetable oven omelet(a good brunch dish)
directions: Beat eggs, milk, baking mix and salt until foamy.
Rinse chilies with water.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle tomatoes and onion evenly over chilies.
Pour egg mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until egg mixture is set and cheese is melted, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla, and peanut butter if desired. Beat until well blended.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: upside-down cherry pudding
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar in a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir well.
Drain cherries; add enough hot water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Add extract.
Mix cornstarch with remaining sugar.
Add to liquid.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour hot juice over batter; spread cherries on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pork pinakbet
directions: Brown the pork pieces with garlic.
Then add ginger and after 2 minutes, add the onion and tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes, until a red gravy is produced.
Add the spices such as salt and pepper to taste.
Patis (Filipino fish sauce) may be added in place of salt.
Then add the vegetables.
Simmer until the vegetables are tender and flavorful.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until casserole is thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pie #1
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Add the pecans and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: miracle whip dressing cake
directions: Dissolve 2-level teaspoons baking soda in a cup of lukewarm water. Combine 1 cup Miracle Whip dressing and 1 cup sugar, beating well. Combine with water and baking soda.
Sift together into first mixture, flour, cocoa and salt.
Beat until smooth. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 13 inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 20 - 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Can add nuts and bananas, if desired.

title: pound cake ii
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavorings.
Beat 15 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for about 50 minutes.

title: marinated bell peppers
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat and add onion and pepper strips.
Cover and cook until peppers are slightly softened. Place in bowl and add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: daube(pot roast stew)
directions: Make 6 deep cuts with a sharp knife into the rump roast (or leg of lamb).
Each cut about 2-inches long.
Fill each cut with one of each:
a garlic clove, a cardamom and a clove.
In a 12-quart pot, mix tomato sauce, water, salt and vinegar.
Add the meat.
Bring to a boil on high heat.
Reduce heat to low and let cook, covered, for 1 to 2 hours or until meat can be cut with a spoon.
Turn meat over twice in the process.
Add more water, if needed.
Add the potatoes.
Let cook for another 30 minutes.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls together on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and onion flakes or salt.
Spread on cooled crust.
Layer on top the vegetables of your choice, finely chopped or cut, such as tomatoes, green peppers, cucumber, zucchini, radish, mushrooms, ripe olives and carrots.
Refrigerate for about an hour before serving.
This is finger food which makes a great appetizer.

title: chocolate snowball dessert
directions: Pour half and half in large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate whipped topping, cookie crumbs and crushed candies.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Freeze 8 hours or until frozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Melt margarine and cook onion and celery.
Add flour; mix well.
Add broth and milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cornbread and mix well.
Mix in chicken.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients and fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: taco casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 6 shells.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add taco mix, chili powder, chilies, tomatoes, tomato sauce and picante sauce.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish with graham crackers.
Mix 2 packages of vanilla instant pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Fold in 12 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread one-half of this mixture on graham crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers, then the other half of pudding mixture.
Top this with another layer of graham crackers.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread mixture on baked crust.	Sprinkle vegetables and cheese over it and
lightly press into the mayonnaise mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal butterball cookies
directions: Cream butter and
sugar,
then	add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Mix
oatmeal into mixture, mixing well.	Roll into balls.
Bake in
a	350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered
sugar	when
still
warm.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: garden medley spaghetti(1.7 mg cholesterol)
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
In medium skillet, heat margarine with garlic.
Add carrots, zucchini and onions, cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
Toss vegetables with hot cooked spaghetti, Parmesan cheese, dill and seasoning.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Make jello and let cool, then add all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half of mixed ingredients into mold.
Put in refrigerator and let set.
Spread sour cream on the top, then add remaining ingredients and let set.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add frozen strawberries and mix gently. Put in refrigerator until slightly congealed. Add nuts and pineapple. Put 1/2 mixture in slightly oiled 9-inch square dish.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add ingredients in given order.
Mix until the dough isn't sticky (can use a mixer).
Roll into balls and flatten with a sugared glass.
Use M&M's or colored sugar to decorate.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blankenhaus chocolate torte
directions: In electric mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until well combined.
Add chocolate and blend to combine.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in whipped topping or whipped cream along with nuts.

title: pork roast sauerkraut
directions: Place the roast in the center of roasting pan.
Place sauerkraut around the roast.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of sauerkraut.
Pour water into pan until you can just begin to see the water in the sauerkraut. Sprinkle apple and onion on top of brown sugar.
Roast at 325° to 350° F. for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine everything except crackers and butter.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with crackers and butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In ice cream maker, combine Eagle Brand milk, strawberries and milk.
Put lid on.
Put ice and rock salt between container and holder, adding ice as it melts. Will not need whole bag of rock salt.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, making 2 layers.
Cool and split layers.
Mix together sour cream, sugar and coconut.
After mixing, reserve 1 cup of mixture to use in frosting.
Spread the rest between the split layers.

title: mikey's cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add 1 cup milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto floured surface; knead lightly.
Roll dough into a 20 x 30-inch rectangle; spread butter on dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; mix well and sprinkle over butter.
Top with pecans and raisins.
Begin at long edge and roll up jellyroll fashion; press edges and ends together securely.
Cut into 1-inch slices; place cut side down into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons milk; drizzle over warm rolls.
Yield:
20 rolls.

title: creamy cheddar spread
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in milk. Add Cheddar cheese and red pepper, beating until well blended. Chill 1 hour.
Serve as a spread on wheat and bran Triscuits wafers.
Garnish with parsley.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream the butter.
Add sugars gradually.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour mixture gradually, beating until smooth after each addition.
Mix in oats and coconut. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: swedish nuts
directions: *To blanch almonds, pour boiling water over nuts and let sit about 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cover with cold water and slip skins off.
Dry on towel.

title: garlic pork chops
directions: Mix flour and garlic in one bowl.
In another bowl, mix the other ingredients.
Dip chops in the egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
Cook in hot oil.

title: spinach-pesto appetizer(makes 16 servings)
directions: Preheat
oven
Lightly oil 9-inch spring-form pan. Squeeze
spinach to remove excess liquid.
Add to cheeses;
add remaining
ingredients
and mix until smooth.
Spoon mixture into pan.
Bake
about 1 hour or until firm.
Cool on wire
rack.
(Can be
prepared
ahead
and
stored covered in fridge up to 2 days. Allow to come to room temperature before serving.)
Garnish
with cherry
tomatoes
and
basil leaves. Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: lemon cheesecake pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine milk and pudding. Beat 2 minutes.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until light.
Gradually add lemonade, continue beating until smooth, 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture, blending thoroughly.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: shells with sauce
directions: Melt the butter in frying pan; fry chicken pieces until cooked completely.
Sprinkle
garlic
powder
and cheese over chicken and stir.
Stir in frozen peas and stir together.
Add the soups and
milk
together
(go
light on milk if you want sauce
thick). Simmer
for 15 minutes.
Cook shells; place on plate.
Top with sauce and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat in milk, then egg.
Blend in butter.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 12 small muffins.

title: yuletide eggnog
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, milk and cream.
Beat well.
Sprinkle with a bit of nutmeg.
Makes 24 servings.

title: caramel rhubarb and dumplings
directions: This recipe is for the microwave.

title: creamy olive spread
directions: Beat cream cheese well.
Stir in mayo.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover.
Chill 24 hours.

title: angel surprise
directions: Variation:
Substitute 1 large can crushed pineapple for strawberries, lemon instant pudding and orange flavored angel food cake.

title: "the best stew" by bernadette
directions: Brown meat in butter; remove and then brown the onions.
Add meat, minced garlic and onions in pot with bouillon cube, water, catsup and seasoning.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Then add wine and vegetables and cook for 1/2 hour longer.
This can be served as is or serve over buttered noodles and sprinkle with poppy seed.

title: aunt gladys's gingersnaps
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Roll dough into medium-sized balls, dip tops in sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Dough can also be refrigerated.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix sugar, oil, salt and egg in bowl.
Add boiling water.
Add dissolved yeast to mixture.
Add flour.
Let rise 45 minutes. Make rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° or until brown.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or pita chips.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In saucepan, mix unflavored gelatin with 1/2 cup sugar; blend in egg yolks that have been beaten with water and lemon juice. Let stand for 1 minute.
Heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Add lemon peel and food coloring.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold into gelatin mixture. Spoon into crust; chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: blueberry-lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a medium bowl, combine egg, yogurt, oil, milk and lemon peel.
Stir well.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until just dry ingredients are moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Gently fold in blueberries into batter.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: "good gosh"
directions: Brown meat. Add beans and rice. Cover with cheese.
Put in oven until hot.
Makes a good meal "quick."

title: gold 'n spice chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Separate eggs; set whites aside.
In small bowl, combine yolks with pumpkin, oil and water.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add liquid all at once.
Blend until smooth. Beat whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until stiff. Fold into pumpkin batter.
Turn into angel food pan.
Bake 55 minutes.
Raise temperature to 350°.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Frost with maple icing.
Decorate with walnuts.

title: english trifle
directions: Trim brown crust from cake and tear into bite size pieces. Beat milk with pudding until smooth and thickened.
Layer in 3-quart glass bowl 1/2 cake, 1/2 fruit and 1/2 vanilla pudding. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 12 servings.

title: party salad
directions: In a heavy pot, boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add jello and cream cheese, mixing well. Then add walnuts, celery and cold water.
Next, whip evaporated milk into mixture.
Place in pan or baking dish at least 10 x 16-inch and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Beat together zucchini, soda, honey and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Add flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in
oven for minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand.
Add flour and other ingredients.
Pour mixture into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: barbecue sandwich filling
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Mix in salt, pepper, relish and brown sugar.
Mm Mm good!

title: white bread dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, celery and mushrooms.
Saute about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Add milk to moisten the dressing very lightly.
You may also add chopped chicken and 1 1/2 cups nutmeats if preferred.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese and simmer until flavors blend, at least one hour.
Stir often.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Place large flour tortillas on a baking sheet.
Top with ground beef, that has been browned with onions and Ortega diced green chiles.
Top with layer of grated cheese.
Place in broiler until cheese melts.
Cut tortillas into wedges; serve as an appetizer.
The amount is up to you.

title: pa. dutch apple butter
directions: Pour cider in heavy pan and boil 30 minutes over high heat until reduced by half.
Add apples. Reduce heat to medium and cook slowly, stirring often to prevent scorching, until apples are soft, about 40 minutes.
Remove from heat and press apples through fine sieve or puree in food processor.
Return puree to pan.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Simmer about 45 minutes, stirring often until puree is very thick.
Ladle into pint jars (3).
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 50 to 55 minutes longer.

title: easy turkey tetrazzini
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, melt margarine or butter and cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and water; heat through.
Stir in turkey, pimentos and parsley.
Beat until just boiling, stirring often.
Remove from heat.

title: apple walnut squares
