directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture (dough will be stiff).
Stir in apples.
Spread batter into greased 13x9x2 inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, walnuts, cinnamon and vanilla.
Spread over batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peach supreme
directions: Cook the peaches (minus 1/4 cup syrup), jello and sugar until well dissolved.
Add gelatine that has been softened in 1/4 cup peach syrup or water.
Cool.

title: butterscotch haystacks(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Line baking sheets with waxed paper. Microwave morsels in large bowl at 70% power (Medium-high) for 1 minute. Stir in peanut butter until well blended. Add chow mein noodles and marshmallows; toss until coated. Drop by tablespoons on baking sheets. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter.
Spread apples in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour water over apples.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: upside-down cake
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch casserole, spread brown sugar.
Cut fruits of choice in pieces; spread over brown sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients like a cake; spread on top of fruits.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for a few minutes; turn cake over in a plate.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place chicken on rack and cook 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently, with soy sauce mixture. Transfer chicken to a serving platter.
Garnish with green onion, if desired.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet, heat margarine on medium.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Drain fat.
Stir in soup, water (or milk) and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: country style apples
directions: Slice off tops of 8 apples and scoop out inside with melon baller.
Reserve apple tops and discard apple insides.
Peel and dice remaining apple.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat marshmallows in the milk until melted.
Add slowly to 3 beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: brown sugar pudding
directions: Bake at 300°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray round 14-inch pizza pan with Pam.
Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar; pat in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla until blended.
Spread on cooled crust.
Arrange fruit:
Place strawberries on outside, with remaining fruit in middle.
Combine juice, cornstarch, 3/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Heat until thick; pour over top of fruit.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs together with butter, sugar, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Mix in oats and coconut.
Pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water, Karo and salt until it boils.
Add raw peanuts.
Cook until honey colored.
Peanuts may begin to pop and turn slightly brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Stir very quickly, and pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Do not try to flatten after pouring.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all the juices together.
Fill 2 small ice trays with mixture and freeze.
Before serving, add 1/2 quart ginger ale. Float strawberries or sliced bananas in juice.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: pinto chili
directions: Sort beans; wash.
Put in a large pan of cold water.
Add salt jowl, onion, bell pepper and taco mix.
Put top on pan and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Put in can of Wolfe Brand chili and/or ground beef or chuck.
Let simmer another 30 minutes to an hour.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add garlic clove and onion. Saute over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes. Do not let onions turn brown; add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; blend to distribute seasonings. Carefully add shrimp and saute over medium-high heat until shrimp lose their translucency, about 5 to 8 minutes. Add bread crumbs and stir until all ingredients are well blended. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add egg, salt and soda (after combined).
Gradually add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips (by hand).
Drop by tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let sit on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine in boiling water according to directions on box.
Meanwhile, beat egg yolk lightly with a fork and add to the cream.
Melt the butter.
Drain fettucine while still hot; place in a warm serving bowl.
Pour the egg mixture over the fettucine. Add melted butter and half of the cheese.
Toss with a fork until well blended.
Add rest of the cheese as you continue to toss. Top with rest of cheese and serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: special potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, sour cream, soup, onion and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with cornflake crumbs; drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: creamy lemon dip
directions: Blend well with medium speed electric mixer.

title: favorite salad bowl
directions: In salad bowl, tear greens into bite-size pieces.
Pour dressing over salad; toss to coat greens.
Arrange onion rings and orange segments over top.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Make well in center.
Combine eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans. Add to sifted ingredients, stirring until well combined.
Spoon batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool bread in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove bread from pans. Cool completely on wire racks.

title: avocado bombay
directions: Saute shrimp, onion and apple in butter.
Stir in chicken soup.
Add salt and curry powder.
Heat over low heat until smooth.

title: turkey and veggie pocket
directions: Combine the turkey, mushrooms, zucchini, onions, bell pepper, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour to allow the flavors to blend.
Place 1 cup of the turkey mixture in each pita half.
Wrap securely and store in the cooler for trips.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix again.
Add nuts and chips; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: family style ham casserole
directions: In saucepan, lightly brown ham and onions in margarine.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat just until cheese melts.
Mix in cooked macaroni and pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: duchess meat loaf pie
directions: Stir soup mix into water. Measure out 1/2 cup and blend into ground beef. Shape beef into 8-inch round patty in large frying pan. Cut into six pie-shaped wedges. Pour remaining soup over. Cover and cook 20 minutes over medium heat. Remove cover. Add Kitchen Bouquet to gravy and cook down.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Cut the crust from the bread and mash flat with a rolling pin. Spread with mixture of cream cheese, egg and 1/4 cup sugar. Roll up. Dip in melted butter. Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: mull's pancakes by donna
directions: Blend together sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and flour. Beat lightly with wire whisk, then let stand overnight in covered container.
Use next morning.
Pour onto hot griddle.
Feeds family of four.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and rice in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.

title: kidney bean cheese dip(diabetic recipe)
directions: Drain the beans, reserving the fluid.
In a skillet, combine the oil and beans and cook over medium heat, mashing the beans with a wooden spoon or potato masher.
After 5 minutes, stir in cumin and garlic powder.
Add the bean liquid and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Remove from the heat and add the cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve warm as a dip with fresh vegetables or tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.
One serving
= 1 starch/bread + 2 medium fat protein + 1 fat.
One serving of 1/2 cup = 319 calories, 16 g protein, 320 carbohydrate, 13 g fat and 429 mg sodium.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease bottom of tube pan and line with wax paper.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts (this is extra).
Sift dry ingredients several times.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs as for cake.
Stir in dry ingredients and vanilla. Stir in sour cream last.
Fill pan half full.
Sprinkle a little more than half of the cinnamon mixture over dough.
Pour remaining cake mixture and sprinkle rest of cinnamon over top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove.
Freezes well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 6 tablespoons syrup.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar in small saucepan.
Stir in vinegar, soy sauce and reserved pineapple syrup.
Add pineapple.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for about 2 minutes.
Serve over beef, pork or chicken.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: country bacon potato salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.

Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy. Fold in peanut butter and cereal. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 14 to 16 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin layer cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla with a mixer on medium speed. Blend well.
Add eggs.
Mix until blended.
Stir in pumpkin and spices into 1 cup of batter.
Pour remaining plain batter into crust.
Top with pumpkin batter.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed. combine macaroni, cheeses in crock pot.
Stir in evaporated milk, melted butter, eggs and milk. Cook on low covered for 3 hours.
Top with cheese slices add allow to melt.
Serves 6.
Can be easily doubled for larger gatherings.

title: canned tomato salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, peppers, onions, salt, garlic and vinegar in a large saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Mix all ingredients and form into 1 inch balls.
Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
Also good at room temperature.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cocoa together.
Add the egg, flour and flavoring together.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour dough into greased pan.
Let cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool a little and cut into squares.

title: potatoes and gravy
directions: Cook potatoes on low with butter.
While cooking, dissolve flour in milk.
After potatoes are done, add milk mixture to potatoes.
Stir until thickened.

title: potato tapa(spanish hors d'oeuvres)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet (I prefer nonstick) heat olive oil and salad oil.
Add potatoes, 1/4 teaspoon salt and onions.
Cook until tender, turning to prevent sticking.
Beat eggs with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
With slotted spoon put potato mixture into bowl with eggs. Mix gently to coat.
Spread in hot skillet. Cook until firm.
Slip onto flat plate, cover with flat plate of equal size.
Invert plates, remove top plate and slip uncooked side into skillet.
Cook until brown. Turn out onto a plate. Cut into 16 wedges.
Garnish with greens (e.g., parsley, dill and thyme).

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine first
ingredients and set aside.
Place 1/2 cooked potatoes
in bowl;	sprinkle 1/2 parsley and 1/2 onions over potatoes,
then top with sour cream mixture.
Repeat with rest of ingredients.
Garnish with parsley. Cover and chill.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients, pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: double chocolate cloud cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°, place parchment paper on cookie sheets. In a mixing bowl fluff 3 egg whites, and cream of tartar.
Slowly add your sugar and then put the tsp. of vanilla extract in the mixture making sure that the vanilla is thoroughly mixed in.
Then take the 2 Tbsp. of cocoa and sprinkle it on top of the mixture. Next you fold the cocoa in and after the cocoa is evenly folded you fold in the 3/4 c. of chocolate chips.
The next step is to spoon out tablespoon size cookies on your cookie sheet.
Bake approx. 12 minutes.
This recipe makes about 24 cookies.
You can have 3 cookies for only 2 points.
Weight Watchers.

title: baked corn
directions: Cook corn according to directions on package.
Add corn to remaining ingredients.
Put in a greased pan or heavy earthenware dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place alternating layers of vegetables in bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Cover with grated cheese and bacon.
Will keep in refrigerator for about a week.

title: holiday salad
directions: Drain 1/2 cup syrup from pineapple.
Sprinkle unflavored gelatin over syrup.
Place softened gelatin over low heat and stir constantly until dissolved.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin in boiling water.
Add unflavored gelatin to raspberry gelatin.
Stir in remaining undrained pineapple, cranberry sauce and Port wine or bourbon.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans and pour into 2-inch mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm, several hours or overnight.

title: halushki
directions: Fry bacon and onion together until onion is transparent.
Place shredded cabbage in skillet with onion and bacon.
Cook noodles in separate pan.
Season to taste with pepper or seasoning of your choice.
Mix all together.
You can put some sour cream or cottage cheese on top at time of serving (mix in or whatever you want). Gives a better taste.
Can be made with sausage or no meat at all for those of you who are meatless Friday folks during Lent.

title: zippy cheese puffs
directions: In small mixer bowl combine first four ingredients.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto cracker.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 3 to 4 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Put shrimp, pepper, celery, onion and pickles through food grinder.
Add seasonings and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: broccoli toss
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion.
In small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Spoon over broccoli mixture; toss to coat.
Sprinkle salad with bacon and toss.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight. Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: kafta beisinieh (lebanese meat loaf)(the same meat mix can be used for kabobs.)
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except tomato sauce, water, potatoes and tomatoes.
Knead until fluffy.
Place into a 9-inch round cake pan, spreading about 3/4-inch thick but higher at the sides.
Cut the potatoes and place attractively on top of meat. Slice tomatoes and lay on top of potatoes.
Mix water and tomato sauce; pour over and around meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Onion and green pepper slices are nice additions.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Shell dried corn from cob (feed to chickens).
Save cobs only for jelly.
Rinse cobs and get rid of chafe.
Cut in small lengths. Boil gently for 30 minutes in 3 pints of water.
Remove and strain through wet jelly bay.
Measure 3 cups juice (add water if necessary to make 3 cups).
Add pectin to juice and bring to a boil.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
After it comes to a boil, boil 1 to 2 full minutes until it comes to a rolling boil.
Pour while hot into sterilized jelly jars.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Boil all ingredients to a full boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour on cake.

title: apple custard pudding
directions: Place bread in small baking dish. Top with sliced apples. Pour over mixture of egg, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place baking dish in cake pan with small amount of water.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: lemony coleslaw
directions: To prepare dressing, combine the mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper in medium bowl; stir to mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 2 cans of soup and broth in a bowl; set aside.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package; set aside.
Pour soups in casserole dish, sprinkle chicken over soup mixture and add stuffing.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot and cold slaw
directions: Chop and/or shred cabbage, pepper, onions, pickles and celery. Mix with other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Mix and shape ingredients in patties and place in baking dish.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Drain liquid off dill pickles and place pickles back in jar. Add 1 sliced onion.

title: party franks
directions: Microwave jelly and mustard on High power for 2 minutes.
Stir. Cut wieners into 4 pieces, add to mixture.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Stir.
Microwave 1 minute on 80%.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, salt and water in large pot.
Cook until chicken is tender, about an hour.
Remove chicken from liquid. When chicken is cool enough to handle, remove meat from the bones. Discard skin and bones.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Add milk to chicken broth and enough water to make 8 cups.
Add chicken and bring to boil.
Add dumplings to broth, pepper each layer of dumplings.
Turn heat to low, and cook, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in 6 pieces; then coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Place in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with onions. Break up tomatoes with a fork and pour over top.
Cover. Microwave at Low for 70 to 80 minutes, rearranging meat after 40 minutes.

title: raspberry chicken(governor whitman's favorite recipe)
directions: In a blender, place 2 cups of the raspberries, the corn syrup and the lemon juice; cover and blend on high until smooth.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and heat until bubbly.
Gradually add milk and heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add to white sauce with cheese, salt, thyme, garlic salt and pepper. Heat through.
Stir in cooked broccoli and serve.

title: asparagus surprise casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add seasonings.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with asparagus, then cheese.
Spoon soup over layer. Heat 2 1/2 cups water and 2 cups milk until hot, not boiling.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon over casserole.
Sprinkle a few dry instant flakes on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Pour broth over broccoli and bay leaf in 3-quart pan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In a frying pan, melt butter and stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook 1 minute.
Stir in milk to make a smooth sauce. Remove bay leaf from broccoli.
Pour small amounts of broccoli and liquid into blender.
Process until smooth.
Pour back into pan and stir in milk sauce.
Heat and serve.
Makes 6 cups.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Stir into Crisco until little balls form.
Add buttermilk.
Stir until mix leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured board and roll until workable. Roll out until about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Bake in a greased pan at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all these ingredients.
This makes a 1 gallon jar of powdered hot chocolate mix.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: coconut butterballs
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and vanilla.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add flour, all at once and blend well.
Add coconut and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Chill 15 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add slowly to sugar mixture.
Then add mashed bananas, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour in angel food cake pan or loaf pans.
Can be iced with ready-made frostings or serve as a bread.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl. Make a well in the center.
Beat together the strawberries, eggs and oil and pour into the well.
Stir together just enough to dampen all ingredients.
Quickly stir in the nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 well-greased bread pans, filling no more than half full.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven 45 to 60 minutes or until the bread is baked through and a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes before removing from pans.
Finish cooling on a rack.
Do not slice until the bread is completely cold.

title: high fiber apple muffins
directions: Combine buttermilk, cereal, egg, butter and honey; mix.
Let stand until cereal softens, 3 or 4 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix just until blended.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake 30 minutes, until browned.
Test with a toothpick.
Let cool on racks for 5 minutes.
Dump muffins onto racks and let cool completely.

title: bowl cake
directions: Cook box cake mix and cool.
Break in pieces and layer fresh sugared peaches, fresh sugared strawberries, pineapple chunks, bananas and Cool Whip.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pour ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
While waiting for this to boil, wash cucumbers and fresh dill.
Place piece of dill in jar and cucumbers.
Fill jar with boiling water and vinegar.
Seal.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute mushrooms.
Add soup, soup mix and cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add well drained broccoli.
Serve warm with vegetable sticks or tortilla chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing as they mix and cook better.
Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole. Put 1/4 cup of margarine and crushed corn flakes over top.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Fold tips of wings to make triangle.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add wings and onion.
Cook until brown, about 10 minutes.
Drain pineapple juice to make 1 1/4 cups or more liquid. Blend in soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, ginger, salt, mace, Tabasco and dry mustard.
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Baste with liquid once or twice.
Remove wings to hot platter.
Add cold water to cornstarch to make a paste.
Add a little hot sauce to cornstarch mixture.
Then add mixture to sauce in pan to thicken.
Add pineapple chunks just to heat through. Pour over chicken.
Good with rice.
Enjoy!

title: judy's thanksgiving potatoes
directions: Combine and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sky high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in mashed berries and water; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Pour into a large bowl.
Chill 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is slightly warm.
Fold in the rest of berries.
Pile into pie shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: veal st. charles
directions: In a hot saute pan add butter; lightly flour the veal pieces and sauce, next add garlic, shallots, mushrooms, tomatoes, pesto and white wine to prevent browning. Next add seafood, sprinkle flour across pan lightly and incorporate well. Add white wine if needed, or becomes too thick. Add demi glace and heavy cream. Cook a minute or two. Season to taste. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves two.

title: eggplant and pasta salad
directions: Wash eggplant; prick skin in several places with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tender; cool.
Peel eggplant; cut pulp into 1/2-inch diced pieces.
Combine eggplant, onion, tomatoes, garlic, oil, lemon juice, parsley, oregano and salt in large bowl.
Toss and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook pasta in boiling salted water.
Drain and do not rinse.
Add to eggplant mixture.
Toss and mix well.
Serve warm or cold in lettuce-lined bowl garnished with tomato wedges, lemon slices and Greek olives.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add water to form a stiff batter. Drop from spoon into deep, hot fat.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Simmer Ragu sauce and soup about 30 minutes.
Mix spaghetti, meat, sauce and cheese together. (Save some cheese to sprinkle on top.)
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: simple stir-fry
directions: Put 1 cup La Choy sauce in a bowl.
Combine chicken and cornstarch.
Mix well.
In large nonstick skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil; stir-fry chicken until brown.
Set aside.
Heat remaining oil in pan; add vegetables, garlic and ginger.
Add to chicken; toss to coat.
Heat through.
Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: pots de creme
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in electric blender.
Heat milk just to boiling and pour over ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high for exactly 1 minute.
Pour into Pots De Creme cups immediately and chill.
Serves 4.

title: rice and mexican corn casserole
directions: Cook rice until done.
Add Mexican corn
and
cream
of mushroom soup.
Put all ingredients in a
casserole
dish
and stir to mix.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese melts and begins to bubble.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat all ingredients except for 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 prepared loaf pans.

title: strawberry refresher
directions: Place all ingredients, except ice, in blender and blend until mixed, then add 3 cups of ice until smoothly blended.

title: corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Heat greased corn stick pan.
After pan is heated, add mixture and bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes 14 corn sticks.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Boil and cook macaroni for approximately 10 minutes.
While macaroni is cooking, heat oven to 400°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat with a mixer until light and fluffy.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberries, sour cream and chopped pecans.
Pour into pan and place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Drop eggs, one at a time, into sugar and beat well.
Add nuts and orange slices to the 2 cups of flour.
Then add.
Pour into deep greased pan.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.
Cut while hot into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.
These cookies are soft when done.

title: crisp little lemon cookies
directions: Mix all together using hands to really blend it.
Make 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass dipped in sugar until about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for about 9 to 12 minutes or until edges are lightly brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine wet ingredients and spices in cruet. Shake well before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together graham cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons sugar; mix in butter.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Pour coconut into 2 pie shells.
Beat rest of ingredients together and pour over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Combine next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Fold fruit into gelatin mixture.
Place in 10 cup mold pan or a 3-quart Pyrex baking dish.
Yields 18 to 20 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions.
Place in large bowl and add other ingredients.
Mix and bake uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen, then baked.

title: cuire pomme et sauciesse
directions: Cut in 1/2 inches and slice potatoes 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick. Slice onions and bell peppers long ways (not circular).
Put vegetables in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Season and toss.
Evenly layer sliced sausage.
Cover and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done (400°).
Toss and fold to mix in sausage and juices before serving.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Blend flour and water in small saucepan.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Cool with lid on.
Cream together butter and Crisco, add sugar, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Add cooled flour mixture.
Beat until whipped cream.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Bring to boil.
Add rhubarb.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Remove peel.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Add more flour if needed.
Cover airtight in large mixing bowl. Store in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Pinch off amount wanted and roll on floured dough board.
Cut into biscuits.
Place in greased hot pan; turn once to get grease coated on both sides.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.
Dough will keep for a week.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and heat over low heat. Serve very warm in coffee mugs.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.

title: vatopa
directions: Cook chicken; save
3 cups broth.
Let chicken cool and debone. Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth;
add
water, if needed.
Add all ingredients to spaghetti when
cooked.
Cook
until
cheese melts.
Put in casserole dish(es).
Bake
at
325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: molded tuna ring
directions: In saucepan, softened gelatin in cold water.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in can of tomato soup and beat.
Heat thoroughly.
Gradually blend into softened cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, horseradish and hot pepper sauce.
Beat until smooth with rotary beater.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in tuna, celery and onion.
Chill overnight.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Take out, roll and cut into shapes.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Rinse cucumbers, onions and celery; drain. Mix all other ingredients; add cucumbers, onions and celery. Mix well. Ready to eat with Ritz or white crackers.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cook eggs, vinegar and sugar until thick.
To this mixture beat in cream cheese.
Stir in chopped green pepper, pimentos and onion.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon into a pastry shell.
Beat other ingredients together and pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: venison chili
directions: Wash beans, cover with fresh cold water, boil and simmer 2 minutes.
Let stand tightly covered for 1 hour.
Prepare meat; cut into 1/2 inch cubes.
Put cumin seed in skillet over medium heat and keep moving until they smoke and turn toast-colored; then spread on flat surface and crush with rolling pin.
Now melt suet or fat in a large skillet (you may substitute enough vegetable oil or other shortening to coat pan).
Add meat, a few at a time, and sear all sides of cubes. lower heat; add onion and garlic.
Stir until onions are translucent.
Add parched cumin seed, oregano and chili powder; stir to coat meat.
Add tomatoes and green chilies. Bring to boil, then reduce to simmer.
Bring beans to boil again 30 minutes to an hour until beans are tender.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Note:
This dish goes well with party chicken.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook peas in butter for a few minutes; drain. Layer 1/2 of peas, soup, pimento, eggs and cheese. Repeat with other half. Top with cracker crumbs the last 10 minutes of cooking time. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream and cookies dessert
directions: Crush cookies and butter together in food processor, then pat over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Chop and set aside separately 1/2 cup celery.
Cover salad and chill for at least 3 hours.
Carefully fold in chopped celery just before serving.
May be garnished with sliced hard-boiled egg, if desired.

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: Roll chicken in seasoned flour.
Dip into egg mixed with water, then into crumbs. Brown on all sides in hot fat; cover tightly and cook slowly or bake in moderate oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Make cream gravy from drippings and pour over chicken.

title: vermont corn chowder
directions: Melt butter; saute onion and celery until tender.
Add potatoes, milk and corn.
Heat to serving temperature.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken spanish rice casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in water, salt and seasonings.
Remove meat from bones in large pieces.
Place in large greased casserole. Quarter sausage and fry in skillet.
Scatter over chicken.
In shortening, fry raw rice until rice is golden brown, stirring constantly.
Drain rice
and sprinkle over chicken and sausage. Add onions, garlic and tomato sauce to hot broth.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/4 hours in 325° oven.
Heap hot drained peas around edge. Garnish with pimento.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat until done.
Drain well.
Add garlic and onions. Cook about 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add other ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Spoon on toasted hamburger buns. Makes about 8 burgers.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients and beat with a hand mixer 7 to 10 minutes.
Put cupcake papers into small tins. In each cupcake paper put one vanilla wafer, upside down.
Spoon filling in cupcake paper on top of vanilla wafer.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until top starts to crack and edges are golden brown.
Let cool.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top of mini cheesecakes.
Refrigerate until served.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat separately.
Saute onions, garlic and peppers.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, folding ingredients occasionally.
Cook pasta al dente.
Top with sauce.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown beef in butter.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.
Put half of noodles on bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole, then cheese mixture and rest of the noodles.
Pour butter on noodles, then put meat sauce on top. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Use a cover for over half of baking time.
Serves 8.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1 package of franks that have been cut into serving sizes. Simmer for several hours.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix green beans and corn.
Put into a greased casserole dish (7 x 10-inch).
Mix soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onions and salt.
Spread over beans and corn.
Mix melted margarine with crushed crackers.
Spread on top of casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: shrimp mull(makes 10 to 14 servings)
directions: Into a heavy kettle, put first 5 ingredients.
Brown bacon and onion in frying pan.
Add remaining ingredients to kettle.
Cook at boil for 2 hours.
Add 5 pounds raw peeled shrimp.
Cook gently for 1 hour.
Add 3/4 cup to 1 cup sherry and thicken with cracker crumbs.
Serve over cooked rice with grated, shake on spaghetti cheese on top (to taste).

title: cheryl ladd's raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and chopped apples. Add nutmeats and/or raisins.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Add all ingredients to large saucepan and cook over medium heat until creamy.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Cook pudding per directions (use milk and pineapple juice as liquid to cook).
Cool pudding.
Stir raisins and 3/4 of whipped topping into pudding.
Measure 1/2 cup crushed drained pineapple and reserve for garnish.

title: children's play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in heavy saucepan.
Pour over heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until it runs loose from the sides and forms a ball.
Remove from heat and put on wax paper; work until smooth.
Put in a closed container.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Leave out tartar, soda and salt if self-rising flour is used.

title: onion rings
directions: Dip onions into milk for several seconds and then into batter.
Fry in hot grease. Add additional salt to taste.

title: black bean and guinoa chili
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Saute onion, peppers, garlic and fresh tomatoes in bean water.
Or use picante sauce, like Pace, if desired.
Add all ingredients to cooked beans, making it as thick and spicy as desired.
Heat through and serve with favorite chili garnishes.

title: chewy fruitcake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix and sugar; cut in margarine thoroughly.
Press mixture with floured hand in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over baked layer.
Layer candied fruit over coconut.
Sprinkle nuts over fruit.
Drizzle milk over top.
Bake until light golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars about 2 x 1-inch.
Yields about 70 bars.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Melt margarine; pour over oats.
Mix with fork only.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt; add to oats.
Beat egg with vanilla and add to oat mixture.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Drop small amounts on foil.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: norwegian christmas bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Pour scalded milk over shortening.
When lukewarm, add yeast, sugar, 1/2 the flour, cardamom and salt.
Beat well for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining flour and fruit.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place until double in bulk. Knead down.
Let rise again.
Put in pans.
When double in size, bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven until golden brown.
When removed from pans, brush with butter.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
May need to add water unless onions, celery and apples are blended.
Stuff turkey or bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: sausage, potatoes and peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place potatoes in a single layer in a 2-inch deep baking pan. Next layer peppers and onion. Top with sausage.
Add water to pan to 1/2-inch deep. Season with salt and pepper. Cover with foil. Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil. Add more water if it seems dry.
Continue baking for an additional 45 minutes until sausage is browned and done.
(Turn sausage halfway.)
Serves 4.

title: chocolate rounds
directions: Heat oven to moderate (350°).
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in nut meats (chopped).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets in preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ritzy hot cheese appetizers
directions: In small bowl, blend equal amounts of mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese to consistency of sour cream.
Add onion flakes to desired taste.
Blend well; spread liberally on crackers.
Place on cookie tin under broiler, until top is golden brown and sizzling.
Serve at once.
Mixture can be prepared ahead of time in any amount. Keep refrigerated until preparation time.

title: grace's baked chicken
directions: Grease casserole dish.	Place
chicken or pork chops in dish and sprinkle with
onion soup mix.	Mix together dressing and preserves.	Pour over meat.
Cover	and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Slice 2 of the bananas; arrange in pie shell. Beat cream cheese in a small mixer bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until well blended. Beat in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Slice remaining banana; arrange on pie.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine oats, wheat germ, seeds and cinnamon.
Mix the oil, honey and vanilla. Pour over oat mixture. Stir to coat evenly and spread in a large baking pan.
Bake for 60 minutes, stirring evenly every 15 minutes.
Break up large lumps and add the fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: black cow(beverage)
directions: Into two tall glasses put 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream. Slowly fill the glasses with root beer.

title: jam cookies
directions: Blend
shortening, sugar, salt, vanilla and egg. Beat until smooth and creamy. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Make center and fill with jam or marmalade.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tiny pecan pies
directions: Combine
first	5
ingredients in a small bowl; beat at medium speed
of	electric
mixer just until smooth.
Layer 1 teaspoon pecans, 1 teaspoon filling and 1/2 teaspoon pecans in each	pastry shell.
Bake pies at 325° for 25 minutes or until filling is set. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chutney
directions: Put all ingredients in electric blender.
Process at puree speed for a few seconds.
Use to spice up your dishes.

title: date bars
directions: Beat together butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy or light.
Add Bisquick, pecans and dates.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan. Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with xxx sugar.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: In medium bowl cut cream cheese and butter into Bisquick mix until crumbly.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead 8 to 10 times.
On waxed paper, roll dough to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Invert onto greased cookie sheet; remove paper.
Spread preserves down center of dough.
Make 2 1/2-inch long cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides.
Fold strips over the filling.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool for 5 minutes before frosting.
In small bowl, stir together sugar, milk and vanilla.
Drizzle over slightly cooled cake.
Serve warm.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Add chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cook on low 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut up smoked sausage and add to rice about 5 to 10 minutes before rice is done.

title: marinade
directions: Combine in food processor or blender.
Blend.
Marinate overnight: chicken, steak (beef, pork or game), turkey (boneless cutlets).
Bake, broil or grill.

title: corn and olive spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and dressing mix in large bowl until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients except tortilla chips. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors. Serve with tortilla chips. This has 1 gram carbohydrate.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Mix bacon and cheese.
Layer spinach, bacon mixture, mushrooms, onions and peas.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Spread over top of salad.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: rice porcupines
directions: Mix
beef,
rice,
salt, pepper and chili powder.
Form into small
balls, about 1 1/2-inches; place in covered baking dish. In
skillet melt fat and saute onions and green pepper. Pour onion,
green
pepper
and tomato juice over porcupines. Cover and place in 350° oven.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: arkansas stew
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put in a big pan the water and all other ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
After chicken is done, let it simmer on low heat.
Flavor with salt and pepper. Mix water and flour to make dough. Mix well.
Take about 1 cup flour and sprinkle on a table or board and roll dough with a roller until dough is flat.
Cut with knife into strips. Pinch strips into pieces and drop into cooker of chicken and broth.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Spread 1/4 of sauce on bottom pan.
Layer 1/3 spaghetti on top of sauce. Arrange 1/3 cauliflower over sauce; sprinkle with hamburger.
Pour eggs evenly over all.
Add another layer of sauce and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Repeat 2 more times, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Lay fillets on large cookie sheet, skin side down.
Sprinkle with seasoning and butter.
Place lemon slices on each fillet. Cook, uncovered, at 350° about 45 minutes or until thin edges get crisp.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix sour cream, pizza sauce, garlic powder and Parmesan. Spread on a large serving platter.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Top with pepperoni.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with chips or bread sticks.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, cinnamon and eggs; mix well.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Reserve 4 cups mixture.
Press remainder in bottom of 10 x 15 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, melt caramels and sweetened condensed milk.
Pour over crust and top with rest of crumbs.	Bake an additional 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: scrumptious easy corn fritters
directions: Mix in bowl.
Let stand 1 hour or more until crackers absorb liquid.
Drop by heaping tablespoons onto griddle or frying pan, cooking like pancakes.

title: sam's oreos
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Shape dough into rolls; wrap in foil and chill several hours.
Cut into slices; put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, cover one cookie with filling and top with another cookie.

title: filling for fried peach pies
directions: Combine
ingredients
and
mix well.
Cover loosely and let set several hours or overnight.
Cook over low heat until peelings are tender and
liquid
is
cooked
away.
While hot, mash with a potato masher.
Let cool.
This freezes real well. Makes delicious fried pies.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Blend soups; heat.
Stir often.
Top with sour cream, chopped tomato and sliced ripe olives.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.

title: poke salad(1900 or older)
directions: Find poke salad in woods or on fence rows; get leaves.
Take home and wash.
Put leaves in water.
Cook awhile.
Pour water off. Add fresh water.
Boil until tender.
Add oil, about 1/4 to 1/2 cup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Some people put eggs in it.

title: any kind of cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli with cheese casserole
directions: Cook onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add milk gradually and cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper, egg yolk and cheese.
Pour half the sauce into greased baking dish.
Arrange broccoli on top of sauce. Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in hot (400°) about 20 minutes uncovered.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Add water to broth to make 1 1/2 quarts.
Cook vermicelli in broth; drain.
Save broth again.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Add to hot vermicelli.
Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cook in 3 quart covered casserole.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add broth as needed to keep from drying out.
Serves 8.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick; blend thoroughly.
Roll into little balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove and drain grease.

title: fried potato cakes
directions: Heat skillet over medium heat with grease.
Mix potatoes, onion and flour to thicken.
Spoon into hot skillet and fry, turning until both sides are brown.

title: margaret's apple salad
directions: Cook all ingredients except apples, nuts and raisins over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Chill overnight.
Pour over diced apples, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.

title: velveeta sauce
directions: Combine margarine and Velveeta cheese in a saucepan until melted.
Pour over cooked, drained broccoli in a casserole. Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Cover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: little ham sandwiches
directions: Take rolls out of pan in one whole piece.
Cut in half so you have a top and bottom.
Mix first 4 ingredients and spread on bottom half of rolls.
Add ham and cheese.
Put top half of rolls on and put back in pan.
Cut rolls into individual servings.
Cover with foil and heat thoroughly, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut boiled eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; set whites aside.
In a small bowl, mash yolks.
Stir in seasonings.
Mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Put into egg tray or platter and sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 16.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend in order listed at low speed in blender until well mixed.
Chill.
Best made a day in advance.
Yields 1 pint.

title: punch
directions: Mix orange juice with 2 1/2 cans water.
Mix lemonade according to instructions on can. Add pineapple juice.
Chill. Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Makes about 40 cups.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Blend Bisquick and milk until smooth and pour over chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for about 1/2 hour or until crust is done.

title: weight watchers layered dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine and press in 8 x 10-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over crumbs in pan.
Mix each pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Spread chocolate over cream cheese mixture, then vanilla.
Top with 4 more ounces of Cool Whip and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
The Stove Top should be prepared as directed on the box using water only.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides) with tinfoil.
Lay crackers flat, filling entire sheet. Melt butter and sugar on stove; bring to boil.
Spoon (do not pour) butter/sugar over crackers.
Put pan into oven for 5 minutes only (looks like the crackers are floating).
Remove pan from oven and shut oven off.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers and return to warm oven for a minute or two until the chips are melted. Spread chocolate evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts and powdered sugar over chocolate.
Cut lengthwise in four rows and then cut each row seperately at angle.
Refrigerate until hard, remove from pan, tear foil off crackers and break into pieces.
You may want to sprinkle more powdered sugar on cookies.
Yum!

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat the sugar in gradually.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add the bananas and the vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture alternately with the milk. Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including oleo.
Pour about 1/3 cup mixture into Teflon frypan.
Spread out over entire bottom of pan.
Scrape edges to turn or flip when pancake is brown.
After both sides are brown, remove and spread with sugar or jam.
Roll into tube shape and eat.
Delicious!

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Combine ground beef, chili and Cheez Whiz.
Heat over low to medium-low heat until cheese melts and dip is hot.
Serve hot with taco chips.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients in pan.
Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Dip tortillas in sauce.
Fill with meat and cheese.
Roll and place in baking pan.
Top with remaining sauce and garnish with cheese.
Heat at 350° until heated through, 15 minutes. Makes a lot and is good reheated.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for about a week.

title: peach cheese cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, margarine, egg and milk.
Beat and pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Place peach slices over batter 1/2 inch from sides of pan. Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and reserved juice.
Beat and place over peaches.
Mix cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
On low speed, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill greased and floured tube pan and place in unheated oven.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes. Cool 30 minutes on rack.
Then remove from pan.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Sift baking powder and flour; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and blend.
Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
(Suitable for freezing.)

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Add meat of your choice.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In large casserole dish, layer chicken, Velveeta cheese (cubed), and Dorito chips.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel and pour over layers.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: festive cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; stir in almonds.
Beat eggs slightly; combine with oil, almond extract, bananas and undrained pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients; mix thoroughly but do not beat.
Spoon into well oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto wire cake rack; remove pan.
Cool thoroughly before frosting.

title: fried pies
directions: Stir together ingredients.
When mixture is a firm ball of dough, put on floured board and knead down several times.
Use floured rolling pin, pinch off pieces and roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut circles with a saucer.
Place 2 tablespoons of cooked dried apples, or other fruits on half of circle.
Season well with sugar and nutmeg.
Fold half of dough and press edges together with a fork, dipped in ice water.
The pies may be finished by deep frying, pan frying or brush with butter and baked in oven.
Old time favorites are apples, apricots or any fresh fruit for filling.
Try them some Sunday evening.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
stir
until
mixed well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.

title: linguine with clams
directions: Heat and pour over cooked linguine pasta.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine beef, eggs, onion, milk, and bread or cracker crumbs. Season with salt and pepper. Place in a lightly greased 5 x 9 loaf pan, or form into a loaf and place in a lightly greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. In a separate small bowl, combine the brown sugar and ketchup. Mix well and pour over the meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good-for-you biscuits(low-fat)
directions: Mix; knead.
Roll out dough.
Cut into biscuits; each serving has 88 calories and 2 grams fat.

title: nina's taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.

title: frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients for 5 minutes.
This frosting is used to make decorative cake.

title: gooey tea cakes
directions: Mix the cake mix, margarine, 2 eggs and pecans together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the sugar, cream cheese and
eggs
together and pour over the other mixture. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle two tablespoons confectioners sugar on top after removing from oven.
Let cool and cut into small squares.

title: coconut cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Reserve 1 cup batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix cream cheese in bowl of mixer at medium speed. Beat cream cheese, flour, sugar and egg until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over brownie batter, spread to cover.
Top with spoonfuls of reserved brownie mix.
Swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° about 28 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: banana whip
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a blender.
Blend until dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Add milk and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir in blender until partially melted.
Add banana slices and blend until smooth.
Makes 2 3/4 cups or 5 servings. Contains 45 calories per serving.

title: rajin cajun seafood and rice
directions: Follow directions on red beans and rice mix.
When red beans and rice mixture is ready and thickening, add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat 15 to 20 minutes until thickens.
Feeds 8 to 10 people.

title: sausage-cheese bites
directions: Mix biscuit mix and sausage to coarse crumb mixture.
Add grated cheese.
Form into balls (size of walnut) and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
May be frozen and baked right from freezer.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate until use. Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all except corn and beans together and pour into a baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup crushed corn and beans.
Mix 1 tablespoon butter and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done or it bubbles.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Return to skillet; add sauces, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes on low heat.
Spoon onto flour tortillas; add cheese.
Roll up to enclose filling.
Arrange seam-side down in a greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spoon rest of beef mixture on top of tortillas.
Add cheese on top and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until peanut butter and sugar are melted.
Measure 6 pints corn flakes and coconut into large pan.
Pour melted mixture onto corn flake mixture and stir until all ingredients are coated. Pour on cookie sheets, cool and cut into squares.

title: easy bayou bog
directions: Saute sausage in regular or electric skillet.
Do not drain grease.
Add chicken (do not drain water) and other ingredients while stirring.
Bring to a boil, then cover and let simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat; stir. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Lightly grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: In 10 inch pie plate, spread cream cheese on bottom.
Pour pizza sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with onion.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with diced pepperoni.
Add sliced black olives, green onion, sausage, etc. if desired.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with Frito Lay Scoops.

title: asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus in Pyrex dish (drain asparagus). Combine remaining ingredients in bowl. Marinate asparagus in marinade for 1 hour in refrigerator before serving. Serve with sauce made of Italian oil dressing combined with mayo. Arrange small white onion rings and pimento strips over the asparagus when ready to serve.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Pour
a
small amount of blueberry filling in pie crust to cover
bottom.
Then slice the bananas on top of the filling. Then
add
rest of blueberry filling.
Then put the Cool Whip on top.
Keep refrigerated until it is all eaten.

title: best of show whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine milk and 2 cups warm water.
To this add honey, oil and salt.
In large bowl put about 6 cups flour, then add the yeast and milk mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Add rest of flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise.
Place on board and divide dough in half.
Knead a minute or two and place in greased pan.
Brush oil over top of loaves and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. To make in a bread maker, cut recipe in half.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain berries and reserve juice.
Heat the juice and dissolve 2 packages of the lemon Jell-O in the juice, adding water to 2 1/2 cups when dissolved.
Add the berries and pour half of the amount into a mold.
Set aside until thick.

title: the best lemon chess pie* * * * *
directions: The recipe for the trout came from the chef at the Loan Air Force Base Officer's Club in France.
Even my no-fish husband enjoys it.
The Stagecoach Inn is a famous stage coach stop in Salado, Texas.
It is situated right on Interstate 35, about halfway between Dallas and San Antonio.
The waitresses recite the menu just as they did over 100 years ago.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet and season.
Pare potatoes and slice thin.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Alternate layers of potatoes and flour mixture in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Dot with butter and pour milk over all.
Top with pork chops. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes longer, or until potatoes are browned.

title: grandma's potato rolls
directions: Mix in order given except for water, yeast and flour.
Add yeast to warm water and set aside until foamy on top and add. Add flour to other ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Knead lots.
Set aside until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Let rise again until double.
Make rolls.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan side by side and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.
Takes 3 to 4 hours total time to prepare and cook.

title: dinner rolls(one of my favorite recipes)
directions: In large mixing bowl, place first 4 ingredients.
Stir.
Add warm water.
Stir.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour or more to make stiff dough.
Stir.
On floured board, knead in approximately 3 more cups of flour.
Knead until dough is elastic and lumps have smoothed out.
Place back in mixing bowl, cover and let rise in warm place for 1 1/2 hours or in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use, punch down.
Make out in rolls about the size of golf balls and let rise 1 1/2 hours in warm place.
Grease baking pans while making out rolls.
This makes 48 dinner rolls and dough will keep in refrigerator 1 week.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Remove bones from chicken.
Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix broth, soup and Veg-All.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter; and pour chicken. Bake in 400° oven until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook celery, onions and sprouts in broth until tender.
Add chicken.
Mix soy sauce, cornstarch and water together.
Add to chicken mixture.
Cook until thickened.
May serve over rice and top with chow mein noodles.
Will serve 10.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Use a deep glass bowl.
Layer as follows.

title: pound cake #8
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Cream sugar, Crisco and vanilla. Add eggs;
beat
well.	Sift
flour;
add
to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crazy slaw
directions: Chop peppers, onion and tomatoes.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.

title: leah's fresh fruit delight
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake in greased flange or large round pan.
Let cool 10 minutes, then invert on plate or tray.
Cool completely.
Spread glaze over cake.
Spoon on fruit.
Cover all with whipped topping; chill.
Garnish with fresh fruit when serving.

title: grandma's navy bean soup
directions: Wash and soak navy beans 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Put on to cook and when it comes to a full boil, add baking soda.
Let it boil about 2 minutes (it boils over easy, so keep heat low). Drain and add more water.
Add ham and onion.
Boil until beans are done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with bread and butter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Add pecans and pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate egg cream
directions: Combine milk and seltzer in a tall glass.
Stir in the chocolate syrup until the drink is blended and a head forms.

title: jam squares
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until pieces are size of peas.
Add vanilla.
Press about half of dough into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread with preserves.
Roll remaining chilled dough and cut into strips and form lattice for top of cake.
Press edges to bottom.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut.
Enjoy.

title: cheesy tomato-bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain green beans.
Empty into ungreased pie pan.
Wash and cut stem ends from tomatoes; cut into slices.
Place tomato slices over beans; sprinkle with salt. Cover with cheese slices.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Add to remaining ingredients and cook until rice is done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Place rice in casserole dish.
Pour butter over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix French onion soup, cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour this mixture over chicken and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Shape raw hamburger into thin patties.
Moisten stuffing with water and add salt and pepper.
Place about 2 tablespoons of stuffing on one raw hamburger.
Seal as you would a pie crust. Place in baking dish.
Pour 1 can of soup over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: public school apple crisp-circa 1950's
directions: Peel apples and remove core.
Slice thin and place in greased pie pan.
In bowl, mix oats, sugar and flour.
Add softened butter and mix until crumbly.
(You can use a pastry blender or 2 knives to cut mixture.)
Pour mixture on top of apples and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together; make a well in the center; beat milk and egg together; add egg mixture to dry ingredients and mix with a pastry blender. You may add raisins, or cheese before adding the milk and eggs and the secret is not to mix too much. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked eggs
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Add 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Bake; set aside.
Mix water, sugar, milk and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in the cake with a fork, then pour mixture over entire cake.
Let cool.
Then spread Cool Whip over the cake.
Put cherries on top for decoration.

title: tuna italiano
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onions with oregano in margarine until tender. Blend in soup. Add remaining ingredients. Heat, stirring now and then, until heated through. Serve with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: okra gumbo*
directions: Saute okra, tomato and onion.
Add roux.
Add desired meat with water.
Season.
Cook about 2 hours.
One cup equals 1 vegetable exchange, 1 fat exchange and 1 meat exchange.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Set aside.
Combine cornstarch and spices in medium saucepan.
Add a little syrup. Mix well.
Add remainder of syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add peach halves.
Simmer one minute.
Cool.
Good with ham or poultry.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk. Add marshmallows; stir until melted. Remove from heat; cool 20 minutes. Divide in half; place each portion on a 20 inch piece of wax paper. Shape each portion into 12 inch log. Roll in nuts. Wrap tightly; chill 2 hours or until firm. Remove paper; cut into 1/4 inch slices.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Combine sugar, water, and cherries and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved. Add pineapple with juice, pecans, and coke.
Stir together and chill until firm.

title: plantation dinner
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in milk, soup and cheese until well blended.
(You may want to add more milk.)
Add remaining ingredients; heat.

title: fudge
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo (softened).
Add evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Stir in marshmallow creme, vanilla and chocolate chips until melted.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into cupcake papers.
Let set until firm.

title: helen's zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir together dry ingredients. Combine with zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
You may substitute 1/2 cup coarse bran for 1/2 of the flour, if desired.

title: french market squash
directions: Boil squash in salted water for 7 to 10 minutes, until soft; drain and add soup, sour cream, carrot, onion, pimento and 1/2 package stuffing mix.
Mix in with butter, salt and pepper.
Put in large casserole dish and top with remaining stuffing mix.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Dice bacon and cook until crisp; drain.
Drain liquid from beans and save in case beans become too dry in cooking.
Put beans in baking dish.
Add bacon and small amount of yellow mustard, catsup and brown sugar to your liking.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan; add brown sugar and heat to boiling.
Add white sugar and sour cream.
Cook slowly to soft-ball stage (236° on candy thermometer).
Cool to room temperature without stirring.
Beat until mixture holds its shape. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour quickly into buttered pan.

title: carrot 'n crumb cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Nilla wafer crumbs, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; set aside. In a large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, blend Planters peanut oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in carrots and Planters pecan pieces.
Pour into well greased and floured 9 cup fluted tube pan.

title: old-fashion caramel corn
directions: Put corn in large roaster.
Remove all up-popped kernels.
Boil for 5 minutes, the brown sugar, oleo, syrup and salt.
Take off stove and add in 1 tsp. soda.
Stir well.
Pour over pop corn and stir really good.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stirring every 15 minutes at 250 degrees.
Spread out on wax paper to cool.
Break apart right away.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine the first four ingredients; press into the bottom and sides of an ungreased 9 inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes or until crust just begins to brown. Cool. In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually whisk in cream; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Gradually whisk half into egg yolks; return all to pan. Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla until butter is melted. Cool 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour into crust; sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Chill 30 minutes or until set. Meanwhile, crush 2 c. of blueberries in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Press berries through sieve; set aside 1 c. juice (add water if necessary). Discard pulp. In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in blueberry juice; bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool 15 minutes. Gently stir in remaining berries; carefully spoon over filling. Chill 3 hours or until set. Store in the refrigerator.

title: 3 bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in large pot and cover with water. Soak 8 hours.
Drain and return beans to pot.
Add all ingredients but spinach and cheese.
Bring to a boil and simmer covered about 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add spinach; cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle servings with Parmesan.
Yield: approximately 3 quarts.
Very hearty and healthy!
Freezes well.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: party taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread mixture thinly on serving plate or tray.
Cover with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and cheese.
Dip chips and enjoy.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Mix in chili powder, basil, oregano and cumin.
Stir in zucchini and carrots until well blended.
Cook for about 1 minute over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chopped tomatoes, undrained kidney beans and drained kidney beans.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until thick.
Top with onions, tomatoes and lettuce or green peppers.
Contains per serving: 142 calories and 30 fat calories.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in salted water; cool and pick from bone.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Reserve chicken broth to cook spaghetti in later.
Grate cheese, reserving 1/2 to put on top of casserole.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onions and beef.
Drain; stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish, then top with green beans and potatoes over the beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato moussaka
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Brush both sides with oil and place in single layer on cookie sheets.
Bake 7 minutes in 400° oven.
Turn. Brush with oil and bake 8 more minutes or until tender.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender; drain.
Cook broccoli in salted water; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased casserole dish. Place halved chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: german style stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cook and stir bacon, celery and onions until bacon is crisp; stir in sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, vinegar and the potatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly 2 minutes.
Remove centers from tomatoes. Spoon 1/3 cup potato mixture into each tomato cup.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Top each tomato with dollop of sour cream.
Bake 2 minutes longer.
Serve immediately.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: extra special chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add vanilla, eggs, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, and stir in.
Add chips and nuts to the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: trade winds salad
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine with brown sugar.
Add luncheon meat which has been chopped.
Cook and stir until golden brown.
In large bowl combine cooked macaroni, luncheon meat, drained pineapple chunks, cheese and green pepper.
Stir together mayonnaise, sour cream (may use pineapple yogurt), pineapple juice and salt.
Add to macaroni mixture and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: parmesan potato slices
directions: Pour oil into baking dish (15 1/2 x 10-inch).
In a plastic bag, combine flour, cheese, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Shake a few potatoes at a time in the bag to coat with the mixture. Place potatoes in a single layer over the oil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn slices and sprinkle with seasoning. Bake until done, about 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: memorable meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except shortening, soup and mushrooms.
Shape into balls.
In skillet brown meat balls in shortening. Pour off accumulated fat.
Stir in soup and mushrooms, including liquids.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until well done, stirring occasionally.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck, drain well.
Add seasoning mix to meat. Shred lettuce, dice tomatoes, grate cheese.
Put all in big bowl. Add dressing and mix together.
Add broken chips to top.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix sugar
and	cornstarch together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add butter, milk and flavor and mix well.
Bake in deep uncooked pie shell.	Bake at 350° until firm and golden brown.

title: unbelievable lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle cukes with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain liquid off.
Add onions and vinegar.
Just before serving add sour cream. Yields 6 servings.

title: marinated beef and broccoli supper
directions: In
skillet, melt butter.
Add broccoli and onion; cook over medium-high heat until crispy-tender, stirring occasionally. While
this is cooking, in a mixing bowl, stir together ginger, salt,
pepper,
lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Add sirloin
strips
to mixture and coat evenly; let stand in mixture
for
5 to 10 minutes.
Add this to broccoli and onion; continue cooking until meat is browned (about 6 to 8 minutes). Serve with rice (on it or beside it).

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar and cream until it forms a soft ball when dripped off spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter to mixture.
Beat well and pour into greased pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Use 1 cup crushed cornflakes in place of crunchy peanut butter, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
