directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in covered casserole dish in 325° oven until done.

title: one step chicken dinner
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (greased), pour in the peas, juice also; on the other 1/2 of dish, pour in rice.
Now you have peas and juice and water on 1 side and rice and 1 spoon butter on the other side.
Place chicken pieces on top of this.
Season to taste and cover.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icing
directions: Pour over cake while hot.

title: toffee bar cookies
directions: With electric mixer, cream brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat until blended. Stir in flour until blended.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Melt Hershey bar in double boiler and spread immediately on hot cookies.
Sprinkle on pecans.
Cut into bars while warm. Makes 24 bars.

title: lush dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Blend margarine, sugar, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: turkey and broccoli supreme
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add stock slowly over low flame.
When quite thick, remove from stove and add other ingredients.
Place thoroughly drained broccoli in large casserole dish.
Add half of sauce and then turkey slices.
Top with additional cheese and place under broiler until bubbly.
Serves ???.

title: southern fried apple pies
directions: Cut the shortening into the flour, using a food processor or pastry blender.
Add the milk and process until mixture clings together in a ball.
Divide the dough into 12 balls about the size of golf balls. Roll each portion to a circle about 5 inches in diameter.

title: white ice cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Alternate flour and milk, beating after each addition.
Add beaten egg whites last. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Bring beer to a boil.
Add shrimp and boil for 2 minutes. Shell and devein shrimp.
Melt butter and add basil, parsley and shrimp.
Cook on medium heat about 20 minutes, turning shrimp occasionally.

title: coleslaw with fruit cocktail
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add drained fruit cocktail and mix with Miracle Whip or mayonnaise.
Mix well to have a coleslaw salad. Reserve a few cherries to put on top.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling
water and cook 3 minutes, beating while cooking on high speed.
Remove
from	heat
and
stir in vanilla.
Covers 2 (9-inch) cakes.

title: haystack candy
directions: Melt chips in microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Add noodles. Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt; add eggs, beating well. Stir in corn.
Add milk; pour into buttered casserole and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir once during baking, just after mixture is heated through and before it becomes set.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugars and oleo.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake on a sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
I bake as a drop cookie at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine bacon grease with onion.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: john ben getthe
directions: Brown meat and onion; mix all together with 1/2 of the cheese. Dot top with remaining cheese.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boiling point.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in blender.
Add to milk, stirring rapidly.
Pour milk over bread that has been put in a 3-quart Pyrex bowl.
Sprinkle with raisins and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a pan of hot water.
It is done when knife inserted into custard comes out clean.

title: fire house ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze according to freezer directions.

title: german chocolate mystery cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with 1 cup water in bowl; mix well.
Combine milk and margarine in glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Blend in frosting mix.
Pour cake batter into greased tube pan.
Spoon frosting into ring over batter.
Do not allow frosting to touch side of pan.
Microwave on Medium for 10 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Bring to a boil. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

When dark streaks start to appear, remove from heat and add chopped nuts and butter. Replace on heat for about 5 minutes again, stirring constantly, until it turns quite dark and is soft-ball consistency.
Remove from heat and allow to stand about 4 minutes.
Add large nuts. Beat until fairly stiff and drop on buttered pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine 2 cups crumbs, 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and melted butter and mix well.
Press all but 2/3 cup on bottom and sides of greased cheese cake pan.
Beat eggs until thick and light.
Add remaining sugar, flour, salt, vanilla, lemon juice and rind; beat well.
Combine evaporated milk and cheese.
Mix well; add egg mixture to that.
Pour into pan with crumbs and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf and few leaves of celery during last 30 minutes.
Cover kettle tightly and do not boil but simmer gently.
Let cool in broth.
When cold, remove all gristle and cut in large pieces.
Save broth.
Cook 1 large box spaghetti in rapidly boiling, salted water until tender.

title: shrimp and crabmeat au gratin
directions: Cook shrimp in salted water for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Drain artichokes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute mushrooms for 5 minutes in 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute garlic and shallots for 5 minuets in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove and stir in flour and pepper, then stir in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring; remove from heat. Add half cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in wine.
Drain crabmeat; remove cartilage; flake.

title: chili beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet and drain.
Add remaining ingredients to ground beef in a large Dutch oven.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough water for the consistency of soup. Simmer for 1 hour or until ingredients are tender.

title: el rancho cafe pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients with wooden spoon and cook on hot griddle.

title: taco seasoning
directions: Cook 1 lb. ground beef till crumbly.
Drain off excess fat; add taco seasoning and 1 c. water.
Cook until water is evaporated.
Can also be used on chicken or any meat item you wish.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream together margarine,
sugar and vanilla.
Add well beaten eggs and flour.
Grease
and
flour
x 14-inch pan. Put in layer of nuts, layer
of
batter, then layer of fruits. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, dump cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Spread cake mix (dry).
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Reduce to 325° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed ham rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half.
Split the whole pan at once.
Spread both sides; cover with ham and cheese.
Put back together and return to the original pan.
Cut individual rolls.
Cover with foil; bake for 20 or 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
You can freeze and heat when ready to serve.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Use electric beater.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and bananas, a little at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Put into well-greased cupcake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Frost with your favorite frosting.
Makes 18 to 20 cupcakes.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine candy and sweetened condensed milk in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until candy melts.
Cool, stirring constantly.
Add about 1 quart milk to candy mixture; beat until well blended.

title: breast of chicken rustica
directions: Melt oleo in 12-ounce skillet; add chicken breasts.
Cook 4 minutes on each side.
Add water, milk and soup; mix and stir. Add noodles and stir to cover with liquid.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring twice, until chicken is done and noodles tender.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown sausage or ground beef and drain.
In double boiler, melt cheese, then add meat.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Pile on bread slices.
Heat in oven about 5 to 7 minutes.
If frozen or cold, leave in oven about 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly (oven, 350° to 375°).

title: southwestern beef brisket
directions: Season beef with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
In a Dutch oven, heat oil; brown the beef on both sides.
Combine water, tomato sauce, onion, vinegar, chili powder, oregano, cumin, garlic powder, red pepper and remaining salt and pepper; pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind bologna and boiled ham fine.
Grind boiled eggs and pickles, medium or coarse.
Mix well with salad dressing.
Spread thick on sandwich (sliced) bread and piece of lettuce.
Makes a large bowl for several people.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Fold capers, pickles, olives, parsley, cucumbers and onion into mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: alabama grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add sour cream and blend together well. Add remaining
ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: ham and cheese snacks
directions: Combine butter, ham, onion and mustard.
Mix well.
Spread on toasted bread slices.
Top with cheese slices.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut in half and serve. Yields 16 snack servings.

title: fred's beans and tamales
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet or electric skillet; drain off excess grease.
Add beans, tomato sauce, tamales and seasonings. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and blend well.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Set aside small portion of flour to mix with candied fruit and nuts.
Fold flour mixture into the batter; blend well.
Add lemon and orange extract and blend well.
Mix leftover flour with the candied fruits and nuts until they are all separated, then add to cake batter and blend well.
Grease either three six-inch pans or one large fruit cake pan.
Line with waxed paper on bottom and sides and then grease again.
Note:
A shot glass can be placed in the middle of small pans, but grease first and then line with wax paper and grease again.
Place in a cold oven set at 250° and bake 3 hours for the large size and about 2 1/4 hours for the smaller size.
Nuts and cherries placed on tops of cake give a professional touch.
Baste with rum, brandy or sherry, if desired.

title: orange lamb chops
directions: Trim excess fat.
Combine orange peel, juice and thyme; spoon over chops.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature or several hours in refrigerator; turn chops once or twice.
Drain, reserving orange mixture.
Brown chops on both sides in hot shortening.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add orange mixture and mushrooms.
Cover; simmer 40 minutes.
Uncover; simmer 5 minutes more.

title: slim waldorf salad
directions: In medium size bowl, combine apples, celery, raisins and walnuts. Stir in yogurt until well mixed. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Cool and crumble.
In bacon grease, cook onion and bell pepper for 5 minutes.
Mix together onion, bell pepper, bacon and brown sugar.
In different bowl, mix pork and beans, mustard, black pepper and catsup.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: triple chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Combine ingredients, except chocolate chips, mixing about 5 minutes on high.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: macaroni pizza(squares; easy to serve)
directions: Combine eggs, milk and pepper; stir in macaroni.
Pour macaroni mixture into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until set. Combine tomato sauce and oregano; spread over macaroni.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 additional minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy mexican omelet
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; whisk mixture just until blended. Heat a heavy 8-inch skillet over medium heat until hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Add butter and rotate skillet to coat bottom.
Pour egg mixture into skillet; sprinkle with cheese and jalapeno peppers.
As mixture starts to cook, gently lift edges of omelet with a spatula; tilt pan so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Fold omelet in half and transfer to plate.
Top with salsa.
Yields 1 or 2 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain spinach until almost dry.
Add cream cheese and nutmeg to the above mixture and serve hot.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over the bread crumbs; cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine meat, salt, milk, bread crumbs and onion; mix well. Shape into balls; place meat balls (uncovered) in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into two greased waxed paper-lined loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli-peas casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange 1 package cooked broccoli in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with peas.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onions and eggs to make sauce.
Pour half of the sauce over the broccoli and peas.
Add remaining broccoli and top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add cold water.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Add butter; cook over very low heat or in top of double boil until thick, about 15 minutes.
Pour slowly over beaten egg, whisking all the while.
Lastly, add lemon juice and rind.
Serve hot over gingerbread.

title: sugar cream cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with crushed corn flakes. Pour melted butter on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes a large dish; great for breakfast.
tags: cream of chicken soup or chicken-mushroom

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a medium mixer bowl, combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm water. Stir until yeast is dissolved. Stir in flour, 2 cups warm water and sugar.
Beat until smooth. Cover with cheesecloth.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 days or until bubbly.
Stir 2 to 3 times each day.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix dressing as per instructions on the package and put 1/2 on the bottom of your dish.
Save the rest for the topping.

title: chicken casserole armistine
directions: Mix all together
and
bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour. Serves 12 to 14 people.
Better if you cook the day before and reheat.

title: savory beef for beef and vegetable stew
directions: In hot oil in Dutch oven, brown beef cubes well on all sides. Remove and set aside.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery to Dutch oven and saute until tender, about 8 minutes.
Return beef to pan.
Add parsley, garlic, tomato sauce, wine, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper, thyme, bay leaf and 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/4 hours. Add vegetables and cook as directed for Savory Beef and Vegetable Stew.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Put sugar cookie dough in sheet cake pan and roll out (this may take the patience of Job).
Cook as directed until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo and pour over baked and cooled "cookies".
You can top the cake with bananas, pineapple, strawberries, etc.
(I use 1 can of cherry pie filling.)

title: festive stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Loosen the skin from 1 side of each chicken breast and insert 1 1/2 tablespoons of filling under the skin.
Smooth skin and tuck the 2 ends under to form a rounded dome shape.
Place, side by side, in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
This step can be done weeks ahead.
Cover tightly and freeze if preparing ahead.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda together.
Pour in water and mayo.
Mix well.
Bake 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.
Put in 7 X 11 X 7 1/2 pan.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil the butter, brown sugar, Karo syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda; pour over popped corn.
Place in a deep baking pan.
Cook at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Add ingredients in order listed, mixing after each addition. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top of cake.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cream soup dry mix
directions: This is a dry mix that can be stored in an airtight container. When needed for soup or sauce, add 2 cups of cold water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
If soup is too thick, add water.

title: mincemeat pie filling
directions: Mix well and place between pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour.
Beat the rest of the ingredients, then stir into sifted flour.
Form into 6 balls of dough.
This will make 6 single pie shells or 3 double crust pies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Batter will be very stiff.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: sue's peanut butter fudgies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in large saucepan.
Add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add butter. Place over high heat and bring to boil; boil 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add oats, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and cool completely.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: biscuit pizza snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Separate biscuits. Put on greased pan. (Can of 5 will be 10 little pizzas.) Cook biscuits at 400° for 3 minutes. Take out and flip over. Add a teaspoon of Pizza Quick to each and sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese bubbles.

title: old fashioned scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel the potatoes and slice (about 6 cups).
Oil a rectangular baking dish.
Arrange some of the potato slices and sprinkle lightly with flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Repeat, making 3 to 4 layers.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add 1 cup sugar, flour and salt. Mix thoroughly.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly. Add vinegar.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Add salt and flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell (9-inch).
Cover with meringue made from egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Chop mushrooms fine.
Combine with cream cheese.
Spread rolls into 4 rectangles, pinching perforations together.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Roll up from long side.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Bake.
Serve warm.

title: brunch
directions: Mix together eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Layer bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour milk mixture over layers.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Put baking dish inside another with water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickled beets
directions: Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar, salt, bay leaf and celery seed.
Add beets and onion.
Bring it back to a boil; remove from heat.
Let stand for 1 hour, then refrigerate in covered glass jar or plastic container.

title: esther's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and grated orange peel.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or so.

title: lickety-split banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas into bottom of crust.
Spoon softened ice cream on top.
Freeze 2 hours.
Top with unheated hot fudge, strawberry preserves, a dollop of whipped topping, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Freeze a little longer.
Serve.

title: short cut fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from water.
Add and stir until smooth and satiny the condensed milk, 1 tablespoon water and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and 1 tablespoon water. Stir until creamy.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter; stir in cookie crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 7-inch). Chill.
In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and undrained strawberries.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into prepared dish.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
If desired, garnish with additional whipped cream and strawberries.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Line muffin tins with paper cupcake liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each and fill with cheese mixture.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: In bowl #1, cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
In bowl #2, mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix both bowls together.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add enchilada sauce, soup, hot sauce and milk; mix well.
Pour Doritos into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour meat mixture over top.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pistachio fluff
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Can be served as a condiment or a dessert.

title: stir fry beef and broccoli
directions: Trim the beef and cut into thin slices across the grain. Cut each slice into thin strips. Toss in the cornstarch to coat thoroughly. Heat sesame oil in a preheated wok or nonstick frying pan. Add the beef strips and stir fry for 3 minutes. Remove and set aside. Add the broccoli, scallions, carrots, garlic, ginger and broth to the wok or frying pan. Cover and simmer for 3 minutes. Uncover and cook, stirring, until the broth has reduced entirely. Combine the soy sauce, dry sherry and brown sugar together and add to the wok or frying pan with the beef and vegetables. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until it is cooked, stirring continuously. Spoon into a warmed serving dish. Serve on a bed of noodles or rice.

title: oven-baked rice
directions: Measure rice and salt into casserole with tight fitting cover or cover dish with aluminum foil.
Boil the water and add to the rice.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes enough for 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot fat; fry until brown.

title: chien chaud(beans n' franks)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towel.
In a bit of remaining bacon grease, saute hot dogs and onion.
Pour pork and beans, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and mustard in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in bacon (crumble first), hot dogs and onion. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring after 30.

title: green mayonnaise slaw
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Mold into a log and sprinkle with parsley.

title: lemon pineapple ring
directions: Drain gelatin.
Add sherbet.
Add undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Add cheese.
Chill until set, about 5 hours. Turn onto plate.
Serve with strawberries.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream; beat until smooth. Blend in sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Trim with reserved crumbs. Bake in 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool at least 5 hours.
Best when made a day ahead.

title: navy bean soup(my way)
directions: Look over beans, discarding halves, discolored ones and stones. In large soup pot, cover beans with water. Bring to the boil; simmer for 2 minutes. Turn off heat and let stand for 1 hour. Drain and rinse. Add water, broths, onion and garlic. Bring to the boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove a cup of beans and liquid; mash and return to pot. Mix flour and butter; add it and the ham. Stir well and continue cooking for 10 minutes. Add hot sauce, salt and pepper to taste. If desired, spike each serving with a tablespoon of juice from jar of hot jalapeno slices. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop into very fine pieces ham, beef and onions.
Mix all ingredients together and form a ball.
Serve.

title: honey sand balls
directions: Beat first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except for powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly, using hands if necessary.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes or until tinged with brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool. Roll cookies in powdered sugar again.

title: cheese spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart souffle dish.
Warm milk over medium-low heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Gradually add cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Blend in melted butter, baking powder and salt.
Cook until very smooth and thick.
Stir in cheese.
Beat yolks in a bowl until light.
Gradually stir yolks into cornmeal mixture.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt in a large bowl until stiff.
Fold into cornmeal and then pour into prepared souffle dish.
Bake until puffed and brown, about 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: clem's chicken
directions: Cook broccoli.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken on top, then cover with cheese.
Mix all other ingredients together, except crackers.
Pour over top, then finish with cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl in order given.
Beat 3 minutes. Bake about 40 minutes at 325°.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: Mix corn flakes with cheese.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly. Do not rinse.
In same sauce pan, combine drained, hot noodles with margarine and parsley.
Add cereal mixture and toss lightly. Serve immediately on warm platter.	Serves 8.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Blend egg and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in greased pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix everything together and press into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Keep some out for the top.
Put a can of cherry pie filling over crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: baked kidney beans
directions: Place beans in shallow baking dish.
Add tomatoes to beans with spoon, then add Worcestershire sauce, molasses, onions and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato pizza
directions: Place tomato slices in a circle on crust, overlapping slightly until crust is completely covered.
Drizzle with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with olives if desired, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle basil over all.
Cover with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Marinate overnight in 1 cup mayo and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat skillet.
Spray with cooking spray or use butter.
Cut 1 to 2 thin slices of cheese and place on 1/2 of tortilla.
Sprinkle with chilies and epayote or cilantro.
Fold and place in skillet. Cook until cheese is melted, flipping 1 or 2 times.
Cut in half and serve.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Spread pie filling into bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Sprinkle butter over cake mix.
Cover with layer of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can serve plain or with Cool Whip topping.

title: swiss cheese broccoli
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over high heat, add water, broccoli and salt to boiling.
Cover and cook 10 minutes and drain.
Set aside.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add butter and milk; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper. Chill.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in margarine in skillet until tender. Add mushrooms; cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Gradually add cream and broth.
Continue to cook until thoroughly heated.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice. Cool jello until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.
Nice in ring mold.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter.
Pat in bottom of cake pan.
Blend with mixer sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs. Pour over cake mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar on top after baking.

title: seven layer jello mold
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve orange juice in 1 cup boiling water. Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup cold water. Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan or glass dish. Let set.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Meanwhile drain shrimp and tuna.
Shop celery, onion and pimento.
Toss all together with cooled macaroni.
Stir in mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate for at least one hour before serving.

title: rose's chocolate cake(great)
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients; heat to boil 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and soda.
Mix with saucepan stuff.
Then add vanilla, beaten eggs and milk with squeeze of lemon.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: banana bread(no mixer needed)
directions: Stir all ingredients into mashed bananas.
Pour into buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 325° oven.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain grease; add tomato soup (no water).

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Line muffin tins with 18 cupcake liners.
Put one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake liner.
Beat the cream cheese, vanilla, eggs and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Pour enough mixture over each of the vanilla wafers to fill the cupcake liners about 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes (cracks on top when done).
Put cherry pie filling on top of each one. Refrigerate.

title: chicken bok bok
directions: Put freshly washed chicken on an aluminum foil covered cookie sheet.
Put tray on top shelf of oven.
Cook at 425° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn chicken over last 15 minutes.
Juicy and delicious!
Easy to make!

title: quick nacho dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until meat is browned; drain.
Add beans, picante sauce and taco seasoning mix, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, milk and cocoa 1 minute only and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla, then drop on waxed paper.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken and 1 teaspoon salt in a large kettle with enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, cover, then reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until chicken is tender and comes off bones easily.
Remove from broth and cool.
Remove chicken from bones.
Keep broth simmering while preparing noodles.

title: tuna patties
directions: Stir egg into mashed potatoes, add onion and tuna.
Shape into 6 patties.
Fry in oil in
skillet.
If used for sandwiches, top each with slice of cheese, or put slice on top of each patty and put under broiler to melt.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onion slowly in a heavy skillet; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hilda's christmas church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in double boiler.
Stir marshmallows and nuts into chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle a double layer of wax paper with powdered sugar.
Form chocolate mixture into a roll on paper; fold and secure well.
Refrigerate until solid and then slice.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate and pour over other 3 ingredients.
Place in a pan and cut after 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes.

title: lucerne spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package; drain well.
Blend eggs with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti alla puttanesca
directions: *You will need to get these cut special.
Do not settle for thinner cuts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with fork until well blended and add rest of ingredients.
Put in a greased 9-inch square pan or casserole and bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats. Let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy. Add sugars and beat. Add eggs. Add oats. Sift rest and add. Pour into greased pan. Bake 50-55 minutes at 350°. Combine 1/4 c. melted butter, 1/2 c. brown sugar, 3 Tbsp. evaporated milk, 1/3 c. nuts, 3/4 c.

coconut. Spread over cake, put under broiler for 2 or 3 minutes. Watch! * I use Grape Nuts instead of coconut. This works very well. May be used as coffee cake for brunch or as a dessert with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil, water and eggs.
Beat well. Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to the pumpkin mixture. Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour mixture into a greased 9x5x3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 65 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain on paper towels.
Crumble.
Break up broccoli.
Chop red onion and green onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar and mix well with all ingredients.
Make one day ahead.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: slimming potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cucumber and tomatoes in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In a food processor, fitted with steel blade, or in a blender container, combine yogurt, cottage cheese, chives, parsley and Molly McButter.
Process or blend until smooth. Add cottage cheese mixture to potato mixture.
Toss lightly to coat. Garnish with additional parsley and onion rings, if desired. Cover and chill. Serve with additional Molly McButter, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
Single serving contains 122 calories and 2 fat grams.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion together in a large electric skillet. Add zucchini and simmer for 3 minutes. Add mushrooms, peas and salt and pepper.
Pour eggs on top of mixture. Stir together.
Let cook for 3 to 5 minutes, then with spatula, turn over.
When it is all turned, spread cheese over top and put lid on.
Cook until set and cheese is melted.

title: open-house punch
directions: Combine punch, citrus juices and strawberries; mix well. Stir in soda. Add punch cubes; garnish with orange slices and serve. Makes twenty-two 4 ounce servings.

title: rose rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat high speed 2 minutes.
Add more flour to make stiff batter.
Cover bowl tightly with aluminum foil.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Divide in 18 equal pieces. Roll each piece to 15-inch rope.
Wind to form coil.
Place on greased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Cover and let rise in oven until double, 1 hour.
Make 1-inch hole in center.
Fill with cherry.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Frost when cool.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: eggs ol
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Bake in a casserole dish 45 - 60 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients in the microwave. Mix the rest of the ingredients together. Place in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add water, mayonnaise and vanilla. Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients except soda, cut in fat until mixture comes to fine crumb consistency.
Save one-half cup of this for topping.
Beat egg well; add molasses, sour milk and soda and mix thoroughly with first dry mixture.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: "pear honey" (jeremy's green jam)
directions: Wash, pare and core the pears.
Slice before measuring.
Put through a food chopper using the fine blade.
Combine pears and pineapple.
Add the lime rind and juice.
Add sugar and cook over slow heat, stirring frequently.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Stir in green food coloring to desired shade.
Pour into sterilized 8 ounce canning jars to within 1/4-inch of top.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Yields 8 (8 ounce) jars.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and Wesson oil well.
Dissolve soda in sweet milk.
Add to mixture.
Add prunes and walnuts.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture; blend well.
Bake in ungreased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato-caviar salad
directions: Hollow out tomatoes slightly, at stem end, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain.
Chill in freezer for 1 hour.
Blend caviar with mayonnaise.
Serve tomatoes on lettuce; top tomatoes with caviar-mayonnaise mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 squares (2 x 2-inch).

title: grilled butter and honey chicken
directions: Melt butter and honey.
Put chicken into aluminum pan and cover with honey and butter.
Put on grill until chicken is done. Remove from pan and place on grill to brown.
Remove from grill and eat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Boil brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and butter flavor.
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water on oats and let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onions and mushrooms.
Drain excess grease. Season with garlic and Italian seasoning to taste. Prepare the macaroni and cheese as directed on the box.
Mix with beef and add the tomatoes.
Pour ingredients into a square baking dish. Top with the cheese. Bake at 250° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, and add milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil a minute or two.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Chop onions, peppers and cabbage fine. Mix all ingredients together; boil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Cut ham into strips; cook in peanut oil.
Drain and set aside. Melt butter in pan and brown the almonds.
Be careful.
Quit when they are just getting brown.
They have to be stirred frequently.

title: lumpia, pampango style(vegetable spring rolls)
directions: Use a 6 to 8 quart saucepan, saute garlic in oil.
Add onions and sliced pork.
Cover and cook until meat is tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sweet and red potatoes, cooking until slightly tender.
Add green beans, carrots, and cabbage.
Mix well. If needed, add broth.
Continue cooking with occasional stirring until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain in a colander and cool.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Combine crumbs, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Dip chops in crumbs, into egg diluted with water and again in crumbs.
Press firmly into chops.
Brown slowly on each side in hot oil in heavy skillet.
Blend flour and remaining salt into skillet and add milk gradually, then 1 cup water.
Stir until gravy boils and is smooth and thickened.
Place chops in gravy.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into medium bowl.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and apples 1/2 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts. Spoon into well-greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until loaf tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: sausage alfresco
directions: Prepare fettucine; drain.
Melt margarine in large skillet. Add onion, then vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Combine sausage, vegetables and cream. Simmer.
Add Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serve over fettucine.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Prepare the night before to allow dill	seed
to soften. Serve with raw veggies or hollowed out bread.
Also
good
with fresh bagels.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add brown sugar, peanut butter and egg.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Make small balls.
Bake in mini-muffin pans at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Have peanut butter cups peeled and ready to put in center of dough as soon as taken out of oven.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Take out to finish cooling on rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: batter fried vegetables
directions: In bowl, stir first 5 ingredients.
Stir in water and egg until smooth.
Heat oil in skillet 1/2-inch deep at 375°.
Dip vegetables into batter.
Carefully add vegetables to hot oil, a few pieces at a time.
Fry, turning once, 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chocolate goodie or triple delight
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar,
flour
and
cups pecans.
Mix well and press evenly
into
a
x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix in bowl cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread
over
crust
and chill. Mix in bowl milk and pudding
mixes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture and chill.
Spread 4 ounces
Cool Whip on top.
Can be frozen.

title: cookie sheet bars
directions: Line an 18 x 12-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Place saltines face up on sheet.
Melt sugar and butter.
Pour over saltines. Spread evenly.
Place in a 350° preheated oven for about 3 minutes or until it bubbles.
Take the pan out and pour the chocolate morsels over it.
Place the pan back in for 1 to 2 minutes, until it melts.
Spread morsels evenly over saltines with a spatula. Spread nuts over all the saltines and press it into the chocolate. Refrigerate overnight.
Peel off the foil and break up into pieces.
For a mint flavor, use mint chocolate morsels, just a few or Junior Mints.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Melt 1/4 pound butter or margarine in an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans and 1 cup coconut in bottom of pan. Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on package.
Spread in oblong pan over butter, pecans and coconut mixture.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar and water; stir to dissolve sugar. Bring to a boil.
Add cranberries; return to boil.
Reduce heat. Boil gently 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add jar of marmalade.
Mix well and let cool.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 4 1/4 cups.
